  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Suffering in Egypt"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Suffering in Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now these are the names of the children of Israel who came to Egypt;
        each man and his household came with Jacob: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Dan, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All those who were descendants of Jacob were seventy persons (for
        Joseph was in Egypt already). '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Joseph died, all his brothers, and all that generation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But the children of Israel were fruitful and increased abundantly,
        multiplied and grew exceedingly mighty; and the land was filled with them.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now there arose a new king over Egypt, who did not know Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said to his people, \u201CLook, the people of the children
        of Israel are more and mightier than we; "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "come, let us deal shrewdly with them, lest they multiply, and it
        happen, in the event of war, that they also join our enemies and fight against
        us, and so go up out of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore they set taskmasters over them to afflict them with their
        burdens. And they built for Pharaoh supply cities, Pithom and Raamses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the more they afflicted them, the more they multiplied and grew.
        And they were in dread of the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the Egyptians made the children of Israel serve with rigor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And they made their lives bitter with hard bondage\u2014in mortar,
        in brick, and in all manner of service in the field. All their service in
        which they made them serve was with rigor."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the king of Egypt spoke to the Hebrew midwives, of whom the
        name of one was Shiphrah and the name of the other Puah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and he said, \u201CWhen you do the duties of a midwife for the Hebrew
        women, and see them on the birthstools, if it is a son, then you shall kill
        him; but if it is a daughter, then she shall live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the midwives feared God, and did not do as the king of Egypt
        commanded them, but saved the male children alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the king of Egypt called for the midwives and said to them, \u201CWhy
        have you done this thing, and saved the male children alive?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the midwives said to Pharaoh, \u201CBecause the Hebrew women
        are not like the Egyptian women; for they are lively and give birth before
        the midwives come to them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Therefore God dealt well with the midwives, and the people multiplied
        and grew very mighty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And so it was, because the midwives feared God, that He provided households
        for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Pharaoh commanded all his people, saying, \u201CEvery son who
        is born you shall cast into the river, and every daughter you shall save
        alive.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moses Is Born'
      title: Moses Is Born
      number: 1
      content: 'And a man of the house of Levi went and took as  wife a daughter
        of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the woman conceived and bore a son. And when she saw that he was
        a beautiful child, she hid him three months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But when she could no longer hide him, she took an ark of bulrushes
        for him, daubed it with asphalt and pitch, put the child in it, and laid
        it in the reeds by the river\u2019s bank. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And his sister stood afar off, to know what would be done to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the daughter of Pharaoh came down to bathe at the river. And
        her maidens walked along the riverside; and when she saw the ark among the
        reeds, she sent her maid to get it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when she opened it, she saw the child, and behold, the baby wept.
        So she had compassion on him, and said, \u201CThis is one of the Hebrews\u2019
        children.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then his sister said to Pharaoh\u2019s daughter, \u201CShall I go
        and call a nurse for you from the Hebrew women, that she may nurse the child
        for you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Pharaoh\u2019s daughter said to her, \u201CGo.\u201D So the maiden
        went and called the child\u2019s mother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Pharaoh\u2019s daughter said to her, \u201CTake this child away
        and nurse him for me, and I will give you your wages.\u201D So the woman
        took the child and nursed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Moses Flees to Midian'
      title: Moses Flees to Midian
      number: 10
      content: "And the child grew, and she brought him to Pharaoh\u2019s daughter,
        and he became her son. So she called his name Moses, saying, \u201CBecause
        I drew him out of the water.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now it came to pass in those days, when Moses was grown, that he
        went out to his brethren and looked at their burdens. And he saw an Egyptian
        beating a Hebrew, one of his brethren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So he looked this way and that way, and when he saw no one, he killed
        the Egyptian and hid him in the sand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when he went out the second day, behold, two Hebrew men were
        fighting, and he said to the one who did the wrong, \u201CWhy are you striking
        your companion?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWho made you a prince and a judge over us? Do
        you intend to kill me as you killed the Egyptian?\u201DSo Moses feared and
        said, \u201CSurely this thing is known!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: When Pharaoh heard of this matter, he sought to kill Moses. But Moses
        fled from the face of Pharaoh and dwelt in the land of Midian; and he sat
        down by a well.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters. And they came and drew
        water, and they filled the troughs to water their father\u2019s flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then the shepherds came and drove them away; but Moses stood up and
        helped them, and watered their flock.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When they came to Reuel their father, he said, \u201CHow is  it 
        that you have come so soon today?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And they said, \u201CAn Egyptian delivered us from the hand of the
        shepherds, and he also drew enough water for us and watered the flock.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So he said to his daughters, \u201CAnd where is he? Why is it that
        you have left the man? Call him, that he may eat bread.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Moses was content to live with the man, and he gave Zipporah
        his daughter to Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And she bore him a son. He called his name Gershom, for he said,
        \u201CI have been a stranger in a foreign land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now it happened in the process of time that the king of Egypt died.
        Then the children of Israel groaned because of the bondage, and they cried
        out; and their cry came up to God because of the bondage. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So God heard their groaning, and God remembered His covenant with
        Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And God looked upon the children of Israel, and God acknowledged them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moses at the Burning Bush'
      title: Moses at the Burning Bush
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Moses was tending the flock of Jethro his father-in-law, the
        priest of Midian. And he led the flock to the back of the desert, and came
        to Horeb, the mountain of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Angel of the Lord appeared to him in a flame of fire from
        the midst of a bush. So he looked, and behold, the bush was burning with
        fire, but the bush was not consumed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CI will now turn aside and see this great sight,
        why the bush does not burn.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So when the Lord saw that he turned aside to look, God called to
        him from the midst of the bush and said, \u201CMoses, Moses!\u201DAnd he
        said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then He said, \u201CDo not draw near this place. Take your sandals
        off your feet, for the place where you stand is holy ground.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Moreover He said, \u201CI am the God of your father\u2014the God
        of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.\u201D And Moses hid his
        face, for he was afraid to look upon God."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the Lord said: \u201CI have surely seen the oppression of My
        people who are in Egypt, and have heard their cry because of their taskmasters,
        for I know their sorrows. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So I have come down to deliver them out of the hand of the Egyptians,
        and to bring them up from that land to a good and large land, to a land flowing
        with milk and honey, to the place of the Canaanites and the Hittites and
        the Amorites and the Perizzites and the Hivites and the Jebusites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now therefore, behold, the cry of the children of Israel has come
        to Me, and I have also seen the oppression with which the Egyptians oppress
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Come now, therefore, and I will send you to Pharaoh that you may
        bring My people, the children of Israel, out of Egypt.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Moses said to God, \u201CWho am I that I should go to Pharaoh,
        and that I should bring the children of Israel out of Egypt?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So He said, \u201CI will certainly be with you. And this shall  be
        a sign to you that I have sent you: When you have brought the people out
        of Egypt, you shall serve God on this mountain.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Moses said to God, \u201CIndeed, when I come to the children
        of Israel and say to them, \u2018The God of your fathers has sent me to you,\u2019
        and they say to me, \u2018What is His name?\u2019 what shall I say to them?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And God said to Moses, \u201CI AM WHO I AM.\u201D And He said, \u201CThus
        you shall say to the children of Israel, \u2018I AM has sent me to you.\u2019
        \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Moreover God said to Moses, \u201CThus you shall say to the children
        of Israel: \u2018The Lord God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God
        of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has sent me to you. This is  My name forever,
        and this is My memorial to all generations.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Go and gather the elders of Israel together, and say to them, \u2018The
        Lord God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, of Isaac, and of Jacob, appeared
        to me, saying, \u201CI have surely visited you and seen what is done to you
        in Egypt; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and I have said I will bring you up out of the affliction of Egypt
        to the land of the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Amorites and the Perizzites
        and the Hivites and the Jebusites, to a land flowing with milk and honey.\u201D
        \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they will heed your voice; and you shall come, you and the elders
        of Israel, to the king of Egypt; and you shall say to him, \u2018The Lord
        God of the Hebrews has met with us; and now, please, let us go three days\u2019
        journey into the wilderness, that we may sacrifice to the Lord our God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But I am sure that the king of Egypt will not let you go, no, not
        even by a mighty hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So I will stretch out My hand and strike Egypt with all My wonders
        which I will do in its midst; and after that he will let you go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And I will give this people favor in the sight of the Egyptians;
        and it shall be, when you go, that you shall not go empty-handed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But every woman shall ask of her neighbor, namely, of her who dwells
        near her house, articles of silver, articles of gold, and clothing; and you
        shall put them on your sons and on your daughters. So you shall plunder the
        Egyptians.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Miraculous Signs for Pharaoh'
      title: Miraculous Signs for Pharaoh
      number: 1
      content: "Then Moses answered and said, \u201CBut suppose they will not believe
        me or listen to my voice; suppose they say, \u2018The Lord has not appeared
        to you.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the Lord said to him, \u201CWhat is that in your hand?\u201DHe
        said, \u201CA rod.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And He said, \u201CCast it on the ground.\u201D So he cast it on
        the ground, and it became a serpent; and Moses fled from it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CReach out your hand and take it
        by the tail\u201D (and he reached out his hand and caught it, and it became
        a rod in his hand), "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201Cthat they may believe that the Lord God of their fathers, the
        God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has appeared to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Furthermore the Lord said to him, \u201CNow put your hand in your
        bosom.\u201D And he put his hand in his bosom, and when he took it out, behold,
        his hand was leprous, like snow. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And He said, \u201CPut your hand in your bosom again.\u201D So he
        put his hand in his bosom again, and drew it out of his bosom, and behold,
        it was restored like his other flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CThen it will be, if they do not believe you, nor heed the message
        of the first sign, that they may believe the message of the latter sign. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And it shall be, if they do not believe even these two signs, or
        listen to your voice, that you shall take water from the river and pour it
        on the dry land.  The water which you take from the river will become blood
        on the dry land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Moses said to the Lord, \u201CO my Lord, I am not eloquent,
        neither before nor since You have spoken to Your servant; but I am slow of
        speech and slow of tongue.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Lord said to him, \u201CWho has made man\u2019s mouth? Or
        who makes the mute, the deaf, the seeing, or the blind? Have not I, the Lord? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now therefore, go, and I will be with your mouth and teach you what
        you shall say.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But he said, \u201CO my Lord, please send by the hand of whomever
        else You may send.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the anger of the Lord was kindled against Moses, and He said:
        \u201CIs not Aaron the Levite your brother? I know that he can speak well.
        And look, he is also coming out to meet you. When he sees you, he will be
        glad in his heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now you shall speak to him and put the words in his mouth. And I
        will be with your mouth and with his mouth, and I will teach you what you
        shall do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So he shall be your spokesman to the people. And he himself shall
        be as a mouth for you, and you shall be to him as God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Moses Goes to Egypt'
      title: Moses Goes to Egypt
      number: 17
      content: "And you shall take this rod in your hand, with which you shall do
        the signs.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Moses went and returned to Jethro his father-in-law, and said
        to him, \u201CPlease let me go and return to my brethren who are in Egypt,
        and see whether they are still alive.\u201DAnd Jethro said to Moses, \u201CGo
        in peace.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now the Lord said to Moses in Midian, \u201CGo, return to Egypt;
        for all the men who sought your life are dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Then Moses took his wife and his sons and set them on a donkey, and
        he returned to the land of Egypt. And Moses took the rod of God in his hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWhen you go back to Egypt, see
        that you do all those wonders before Pharaoh which I have put in your hand.
        But I will harden his heart, so that he will not let the people go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then you shall say to Pharaoh, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CIsrael
        is My son, My firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So I say to you, let My son go that he may serve Me. But if you refuse
        to let him go, indeed I will kill your son, your firstborn.\u201D \u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And it came to pass on the way, at the encampment, that the Lord 
        met him and sought to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Zipporah took a sharp stone and cut off the foreskin of her
        son and cast it at Moses\u2019 feet, and said, \u201CSurely you are a husband
        of blood to me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So He let him go. Then she said, \u201CYou  are a husband of blood!\u201D\u2014because
        of the circumcision."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And the Lord said to Aaron, \u201CGo into the wilderness to meet
        Moses.\u201D So he went and met him on the mountain of God, and kissed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Moses told Aaron all the words of the Lord who had sent him, and
        all the signs which He had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Moses and Aaron went and gathered together all the elders of
        the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Aaron spoke all the words which the Lord had spoken to Moses.
        Then he did the signs in the sight of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: So the people believed; and when they heard that the Lord had visited
        the children of Israel and that He had looked on their affliction, then they
        bowed their heads and worshiped.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: First Encounter with Pharaoh'
      title: First Encounter with Pharaoh
      number: 1
      content: "Afterward Moses and Aaron went in and told Pharaoh, \u201CThus says
        the Lord God of Israel: \u2018Let My people go, that they may hold a feast
        to Me in the wilderness.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Pharaoh said, \u201CWho is the Lord, that I should obey His voice
        to let Israel go? I do not know the Lord, nor will I let Israel go.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So they said, \u201CThe God of the Hebrews has met with us. Please,
        let us go three days\u2019 journey into the desert and sacrifice to the Lord
        our God, lest He fall upon us with pestilence or with the sword.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king of Egypt said to them, \u201CMoses and Aaron, why do
        you take the people from their work? Get back to your labor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Pharaoh said, \u201CLook, the people of the land are  many now,
        and you make them rest from their labor!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the same day Pharaoh commanded the taskmasters of the people and
        their officers, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou shall no longer give the people straw to make brick as
        before. Let them go and gather straw for themselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And you shall lay on them the quota of bricks which they made before.
        You shall not reduce it. For they are idle; therefore they cry out, saying,
        \u2018Let us go and sacrifice to our God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Let more work be laid on the men, that they may labor in it, and
        let them not regard false words.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the taskmasters of the people and their officers went out and
        spoke to the people, saying, \u201CThus says Pharaoh: \u2018I will not give
        you straw. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Go, get yourselves straw where you can find it; yet none of your
        work will be reduced.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the people were scattered abroad throughout all the land of Egypt
        to gather stubble instead of straw. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the taskmasters forced them to hurry, saying, \u201CFulfill your
        work, your daily quota, as when there was straw.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Also the officers of the children of Israel, whom Pharaoh\u2019s
        taskmasters had set over them, were beaten and were asked, \u201CWhy have
        you not fulfilled your task in making brick both yesterday and today, as
        before?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the officers of the children of Israel came and cried out to
        Pharaoh, saying, \u201CWhy are you dealing thus with your servants? "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "There is no straw given to your servants, and they say to us, \u2018Make
        brick!\u2019 And indeed your servants are beaten, but the fault is in your
        own people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But he said, \u201CYou are idle! Idle! Therefore you say, \u2018Let
        us go and sacrifice to the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore go now and work; for no straw shall be given you, yet you
        shall deliver the quota of bricks.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the officers of the children of Israel saw that they were in
        trouble after it was said, \u201CYou shall not reduce any bricks from your
        daily quota.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then, as they came out from Pharaoh, they met Moses and Aaron who
        stood there to meet them. '
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Israel\u2019s Deliverance Assured"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Deliverance Assured"
      number: 21
      content: "And they said to them, \u201CLet the Lord look on you and judge,
        because you have made us abhorrent in the sight of Pharaoh and in the sight
        of his servants, to put a sword in their hand to kill us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Moses returned to the Lord and said, \u201CLord, why have You
        brought trouble on this people? Why is it You have sent me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in Your name, he has done evil
        to this people; neither have You delivered Your people at all.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CNow you shall see what I will
        do to Pharaoh. For with a strong hand he will let them go, and with a strong
        hand he will drive them out of his land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And God spoke to Moses and said to him: \u201CI am the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I appeared to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, as God Almighty, but
        by My name Lord I was not known to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I have also established My covenant with them, to give them the land
        of Canaan, the land of their pilgrimage, in which they were strangers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I have also heard the groaning of the children of Israel whom
        the Egyptians keep in bondage, and I have remembered My covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore say to the children of Israel: \u2018I am the Lord; I will
        bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, I will rescue you
        from their bondage, and I will redeem you with an outstretched arm and with
        great judgments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will take you as My people, and I will be your God. Then you shall
        know that I am the Lord your God who brings you out from under the burdens
        of the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I will bring you into the land which I swore to give to Abraham,
        Isaac, and Jacob; and I will give it to you as a heritage: I am the Lord.\u2019
        \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So Moses spoke thus to the children of Israel; but they did not heed
        Moses, because of anguish of spirit and cruel bondage.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CGo in, tell Pharaoh king of Egypt to let the children of Israel
        go out of his land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Moses spoke before the Lord, saying, \u201CThe children of Israel
        have not heeded me. How then shall Pharaoh heed me, for I am of uncircumcised
        lips?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Family of Moses and Aaron'
      title: The Family of Moses and Aaron
      number: 13
      content: Then the Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron, and gave them a command for
        the children of Israel and for Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring the children
        of Israel out of the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "These are the heads of their fathers\u2019 houses: The sons of Reuben,
        the firstborn of Israel, were Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. These are
        the families of Reuben. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the sons of Simeon were Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and
        Shaul the son of a Canaanite woman. These are the families of Simeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These are the names of the sons of Levi according to their generations:
        Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. And the years of the life of Levi were one hundred
        and thirty-seven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Gershon were Libni and Shimi according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the sons of Kohath were Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. And
        the years of the life of Kohath were one hundred and thirty-three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The sons of Merari were Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of
        Levi according to their generations.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Amram took for himself Jochebed, his father\u2019s sister, as
        wife; and she bore him Aaron and Moses. And the years of the life of Amram
        were one hundred and thirty-seven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Izhar were Korah, Nepheg, and Zichri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the sons of Uzziel were Mishael, Elzaphan, and Zithri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Aaron took to himself Elisheba, daughter of Amminadab, sister of
        Nahshon, as wife; and she bore him Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the sons of Korah were Assir, Elkanah, and Abiasaph. These are
        the families of the Korahites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Eleazar, Aaron\u2019s son, took for himself one of the daughters
        of Putiel as wife; and she bore him Phinehas. These are the heads of the
        fathers\u2019 houses of the Levites according to their families."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "These are  the  same Aaron and Moses to whom the Lord said, \u201CBring
        out the children of Israel from the land of Egypt according to their armies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Aaron Is Moses\u2019s Spokesman"
      title: "Aaron Is Moses\u2019s Spokesman"
      number: 27
      content: These are the ones who spoke to Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring out
        the children of Israel from Egypt. These are  the  same Moses and Aaron.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And it came to pass, on the day the Lord spoke to Moses in the land
        of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, \u201CI am the Lord. Speak
        to Pharaoh king of Egypt all that I say to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But Moses said before the Lord, \u201CBehold, I am of uncircumcised
        lips, and how shall Pharaoh heed me?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "So the Lord said to Moses: \u201CSee, I have made you as God to Pharaoh,
        and Aaron your brother shall be your prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall speak all that I command you. And Aaron your brother shall
        tell Pharaoh to send the children of Israel out of his land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I will harden Pharaoh\u2019s heart, and multiply My signs and
        My wonders in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Pharaoh will not heed you, so that I may lay My hand on Egypt
        and bring My armies and My people, the children of Israel, out of the land
        of Egypt by great judgments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Egyptians shall know that I am the Lord, when I stretch out
        My hand on Egypt and bring out the children of Israel from among them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Moses and Aaron did so; just as the Lord commanded them, so
        they did. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Aaron\u2019s Miraculous Rod"
      title: "Aaron\u2019s Miraculous Rod"
      number: 7
      content: And Moses was  eighty years old and Aaron eighty-three years old when
        they spoke to Pharaoh.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen Pharaoh speaks to you, saying, \u2018Show a miracle for
        yourselves,\u2019 then you shall say to Aaron, \u2018Take your rod and cast
        it before Pharaoh, and let it become a serpent.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So Moses and Aaron went in to Pharaoh, and they did so, just as the
        Lord commanded. And Aaron cast down his rod before Pharaoh and before his
        servants, and it became a serpent.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Pharaoh also called the wise men and the sorcerers; so the magicians
        of Egypt, they also did in like manner with their enchantments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For every man threw down his rod, and they became serpents. But Aaron\u2019s
        rod swallowed up their rods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The First Plague: Waters Become Blood'
      title: 'The First Plague: Waters Become Blood'
      number: 13
      content: "And Pharaoh\u2019s heart grew hard, and he did not heed them, as
        the Lord had said."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the Lord said to Moses: \u201CPharaoh\u2019s heart is hard; he
        refuses to let the people go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Go to Pharaoh in the morning, when he goes out to the water, and
        you shall stand by the river\u2019s bank to meet him; and the rod which was
        turned to a serpent you shall take in your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And you shall say to him, \u2018The Lord God of the Hebrews has sent
        me to you, saying, \u201CLet My people go, that they may serve Me in the
        wilderness\u201D; but indeed, until now you would not hear! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u201CBy this you shall know that I am the Lord.
        Behold, I will strike the waters which are in the river with the rod that
        is in my hand, and they shall be turned to blood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the fish that are in the river shall die, the river shall stink,
        and the Egyptians will loathe to drink the water of the river.\u201D \u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Lord spoke to Moses, \u201CSay to Aaron, \u2018Take your
        rod and stretch out your hand over the waters of Egypt, over their streams,
        over their rivers, over their ponds, and over all their pools of water, that
        they may become blood. And there shall be blood throughout all the land of
        Egypt, both in buckets  of wood and pitchers  of stone.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Moses and Aaron did so, just as the Lord commanded. So he lifted
        up the rod and struck the waters that were in the river, in the sight of
        Pharaoh and in the sight of his servants. And all the waters that were in
        the river were turned to blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The fish that were in the river died, the river stank, and the Egyptians
        could not drink the water of the river. So there was blood throughout all
        the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the magicians of Egypt did so with their enchantments; and Pharaoh\u2019s
        heart grew hard, and he did not heed them, as the Lord had said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Pharaoh turned and went into his house. Neither was his heart
        moved by this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So all the Egyptians dug all around the river for water to drink,
        because they could not drink the water of the river. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And seven days passed after the Lord had struck the river.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Second Plague: Frogs'
      title: 'The Second Plague: Frogs'
      number: 1
      content: "And the Lord spoke to Moses, \u201CGo to Pharaoh and say to him,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CLet My people go, that they may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But if you refuse to let them go, behold, I will smite all your territory
        with frogs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the river shall bring forth frogs abundantly, which shall go up
        and come into your house, into your bedroom, on your bed, into the houses
        of your servants, on your people, into your ovens, and into your kneading
        bowls. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the frogs shall come up on you, on your people, and on all your
        servants.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Lord spoke to Moses, \u201CSay to Aaron, \u2018Stretch out
        your hand with your rod over the streams, over the rivers, and over the ponds,
        and cause frogs to come up on the land of Egypt.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Aaron stretched out his hand over the waters of Egypt, and the
        frogs came up and covered the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And the magicians did so with their enchantments, and brought up frogs
        on the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron, and said, \u201CEntreat
        the Lord that He may take away the frogs from me and from my people; and
        I will let the people go, that they may sacrifice to the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Moses said to Pharaoh, \u201CAccept the honor of saying when
        I shall intercede for you, for your servants, and for your people, to destroy
        the frogs from you and your houses, that they may remain in the river only.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he said, \u201CTomorrow.\u201D And he said, \u201CLet  it  be
        according to your word, that you may know that there  is no one like the
        Lord our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the frogs shall depart from you, from your houses, from your
        servants, and from your people. They shall remain in the river only.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Moses and Aaron went out from Pharaoh. And Moses cried out to
        the Lord concerning the frogs which He had brought against Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the Lord did according to the word of Moses. And the frogs died
        out of the houses, out of the courtyards, and out of the fields. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They gathered them together in heaps, and the land stank. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Third Plague: Lice'
      title: 'The Third Plague: Lice'
      number: 15
      content: But when Pharaoh saw that there was relief, he hardened his heart
        and did not heed them, as the Lord had said.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So the Lord said to Moses, \u201CSay to Aaron, \u2018Stretch out
        your rod, and strike the dust of the land, so that it may become lice throughout
        all the land of Egypt.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And they did so. For Aaron stretched out his hand with his rod and
        struck the dust of the earth, and it became lice on man and beast. All the
        dust of the land became lice throughout all the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the magicians so worked with their enchantments to bring forth
        lice, but they could not. So there were lice on man and beast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Fourth Plague: Flies'
      title: 'The Fourth Plague: Flies'
      number: 19
      content: "Then the magicians said to Pharaoh, \u201CThis is  the finger of
        God.\u201D But Pharaoh\u2019s heart grew hard, and he did not heed them,
        just as the Lord had said."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CRise early in the morning and stand
        before Pharaoh as he comes out to the water. Then say to him, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord: \u201CLet My people go, that they may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Or else, if you will not let My people go, behold, I will send swarms
        of  flies on you and your servants, on your people and into your houses.
        The houses of the Egyptians shall be full of swarms of  flies, and also the
        ground on which they stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And in that day I will set apart the land of Goshen, in which My
        people dwell, that no swarms of  flies shall be there, in order that you
        may know that I am the Lord in the midst of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will make a difference between My people and your people. Tomorrow
        this sign shall be.\u201D \u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the Lord did so. Thick swarms of  flies came into the house of
        Pharaoh, into his servants\u2019 houses, and into all the land of Egypt.
        The land was corrupted because of the swarms of  flies."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron, and said, \u201CGo, sacrifice
        to your God in the land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Moses said, \u201CIt is not right to do so, for we would be sacrificing
        the abomination of the Egyptians to the Lord our God. If we sacrifice the
        abomination of the Egyptians before their eyes, then will they not stone
        us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "We will go three days\u2019 journey into the wilderness and sacrifice
        to the Lord our God as He will command us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Pharaoh said, \u201CI will let you go, that you may sacrifice
        to the Lord your God in the wilderness; only you shall not go very far away.
        Intercede for me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CIndeed I am going out from you, and I will
        entreat the Lord, that the swarms of  flies may depart tomorrow from Pharaoh,
        from his servants, and from his people. But let Pharaoh not deal deceitfully
        anymore in not letting the people go to sacrifice to the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So Moses went out from Pharaoh and entreated the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the Lord did according to the word of Moses; He removed the swarms
        of  flies from Pharaoh, from his servants, and from his people. Not one remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: But Pharaoh hardened his heart at this time also; neither would he
        let the people go.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fifth Plague: Livestock Diseased'
      title: 'The Fifth Plague: Livestock Diseased'
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo in to Pharaoh and tell him,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord God of the Hebrews: \u201CLet My people go, that
        they may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if you refuse to let them go, and still hold them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "behold, the hand of the Lord will be on your cattle in the field,
        on the horses, on the donkeys, on the camels, on the oxen, and on the sheep\u2014a
        very severe pestilence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the Lord will make a difference between the livestock of Israel
        and the livestock of Egypt. So nothing shall die of all that belongs to the
        children of Israel.\u201D \u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Lord appointed a set time, saying, \u201CTomorrow the Lord
        will do this thing in the land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the Lord did this thing on the next day, and all the livestock
        of Egypt died; but of the livestock of the children of Israel, not one died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Sixth Plague: Boils'
      title: 'The Sixth Plague: Boils'
      number: 7
      content: Then Pharaoh sent, and indeed, not even one of the livestock of the
        Israelites was dead. But the heart of Pharaoh became hard, and he did not
        let the people go.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, \u201CTake for yourselves handfuls
        of ashes from a furnace, and let Moses scatter it toward the heavens in the
        sight of Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And it will become fine dust in all the land of Egypt, and it will
        cause boils that break out in sores on man and beast throughout all the land
        of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then they took ashes from the furnace and stood before Pharaoh, and
        Moses scattered them toward heaven. And they caused boils that break out
        in sores on man and beast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the magicians could not stand before Moses because of the boils,
        for the boils were on the magicians and on all the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Seventh Plague: Hail'
      title: 'The Seventh Plague: Hail'
      number: 12
      content: But the Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh; and he did not heed them,
        just as the Lord had spoken to Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CRise early in the morning and
        stand before Pharaoh, and say to him, \u2018Thus says the Lord God of the
        Hebrews: \u201CLet My people go, that they may serve Me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'for at this time I will send all My plagues to your very heart, and
        on your servants and on your people, that you may know that there  is none
        like Me in all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now if I had stretched out My hand and struck you and your people
        with pestilence, then you would have been cut off from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But indeed for this purpose I have raised you up, that I may show
        My power in you, and that My name may be declared in all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As yet you exalt yourself against My people in that you will not
        let them go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Behold, tomorrow about this time I will cause very heavy hail to
        rain down, such as has not been in Egypt since its founding until now. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore send now and gather your livestock and all that you have
        in the field, for the hail shall come down on every man and every animal
        which is found in the field and is not brought home; and they shall die.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He who feared the word of the Lord among the servants of Pharaoh
        made his servants and his livestock flee to the houses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But he who did not regard the word of the Lord left his servants and
        his livestock in the field.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand toward heaven,
        that there may be hail in all the land of Egypt\u2014on man, on beast, and
        on every herb of the field, throughout the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Moses stretched out his rod toward heaven; and the Lord sent
        thunder and hail, and fire darted to the ground. And the Lord rained hail
        on the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So there was hail, and fire mingled with the hail, so very heavy
        that there was none like it in all the land of Egypt since it became a nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the hail struck throughout the whole land of Egypt, all that
        was in the field, both man and beast; and the hail struck every herb of the
        field and broke every tree of the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Only in the land of Goshen, where the children of Israel were, there
        was no hail.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Pharaoh sent and called for Moses and Aaron, and said to them,
        \u201CI have sinned this time. The Lord  is righteous, and my people and
        I are wicked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Entreat the Lord, that there may be no more mighty thundering and
        hail, for it  is enough. I will let you go, and you shall stay no longer.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Moses said to him, \u201CAs soon as I have gone out of the city,
        I will spread out my hands to the Lord; the thunder will cease, and there
        will be no more hail, that you may know that the earth is the Lord\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But as for you and your servants, I know that you will not yet fear
        the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the flax and the barley were struck, for the barley was in the
        head and the flax was in bud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: But the wheat and the spelt were not struck, for they are late crops.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So Moses went out of the city from Pharaoh and spread out his hands
        to the Lord; then the thunder and the hail ceased, and the rain was not poured
        on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And when Pharaoh saw that the rain, the hail, and the thunder had
        ceased, he sinned yet more; and he hardened his heart, he and his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: So the heart of Pharaoh was hard; neither would he let the children
        of Israel go, as the Lord had spoken by Moses.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Eighth Plague: Locusts'
      title: 'The Eighth Plague: Locusts'
      number: 1
      content: "Now the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo in to Pharaoh; for I have hardened
        his heart and the hearts of his servants, that I may show these signs of
        Mine before him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and that you may tell in the hearing of your son and your son\u2019s
        son the mighty things I have done in Egypt, and My signs which I have done
        among them, that you may know that I am the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Moses and Aaron came in to Pharaoh and said to him, \u201CThus
        says the Lord God of the Hebrews: \u2018How long will you refuse to humble
        yourself before Me? Let My people go, that they may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Or else, if you refuse to let My people go, behold, tomorrow I will
        bring locusts into your territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they shall cover the face of the earth, so that no one will be
        able to see the earth; and they shall eat the residue of what is left, which
        remains to you from the hail, and they shall eat every tree which grows up
        for you out of the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They shall fill your houses, the houses of all your servants, and
        the houses of all the Egyptians\u2014which neither your fathers nor your
        fathers\u2019 fathers have seen, since the day that they were on the earth
        to this day.\u2019 \u201D And he turned and went out from Pharaoh."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Pharaoh\u2019s servants said to him, \u201CHow long shall this
        man be a snare to us? Let the men go, that they may serve the Lord their
        God. Do you not yet know that Egypt is destroyed?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Moses and Aaron were brought again to Pharaoh, and he said to
        them, \u201CGo, serve the Lord your God. Who are the ones that are going?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Moses said, \u201CWe will go with our young and our old; with
        our sons and our daughters, with our flocks and our herds we will go, for
        we must hold a feast to the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CThe Lord had better be with you when
        I let you and your little ones go! Beware, for evil is ahead of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Not so! Go now, you who  are men, and serve the Lord, for that is
        what you desired.\u201D And they were driven out from Pharaoh\u2019s presence."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand over the
        land of Egypt for the locusts, that they may come upon the land of Egypt,
        and eat every herb of the land\u2014all that the hail has left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Moses stretched out his rod over the land of Egypt, and the Lord
        brought an east wind on the land all that day and all that night. When it
        was morning, the east wind brought the locusts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the locusts went up over all the land of Egypt and rested on
        all the territory of Egypt. They  were very severe; previously there had
        been no such locusts as they, nor shall there be such after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: For they covered the face of the whole earth, so that the land was
        darkened; and they ate every herb of the land and all the fruit of the trees
        which the hail had left. So there remained nothing green on the trees or
        on the plants of the field throughout all the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron in haste, and said, \u201CI
        have sinned against the Lord your God and against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now therefore, please forgive my sin only this once, and entreat
        the Lord your God, that He may take away from me this death only.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So he went out from Pharaoh and entreated the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the Lord turned a very strong west wind, which took the locusts
        away and blew them into the Red Sea. There remained not one locust in all
        the territory of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Ninth Plague: Darkness'
      title: 'The Ninth Plague: Darkness'
      number: 20
      content: "But the Lord  hardened Pharaoh\u2019s heart, and he did not let the
        children of Israel go."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand toward heaven,
        that there may be darkness over the land of Egypt, darkness which may even
        be felt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Moses stretched out his hand toward heaven, and there was thick
        darkness in all the land of Egypt three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: They did not see one another; nor did anyone rise from his place for
        three days. But all the children of Israel had light in their dwellings.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Pharaoh called to Moses and said, \u201CGo, serve the Lord;
        only let your flocks and your herds be kept back. Let your little ones also
        go with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Moses said, \u201CYou must also give us sacrifices and burnt
        offerings, that we may sacrifice to the Lord our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Our livestock also shall go with us; not a hoof shall be left behind.
        For we must take some of them to serve the Lord our God, and even we do not
        know with what we must serve the Lord until we arrive there.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But the Lord  hardened Pharaoh\u2019s heart, and he would not let
        them go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to him, \u201CGet away from me! Take heed to yourself
        and see my face no more! For in the day you see my face you shall die!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Moses said, \u201CYou have spoken well. I will never see your
        face again.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Death of the Firstborn Announced'
      title: Death of the Firstborn Announced
      number: 1
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CI will bring one more plague on
        Pharaoh and on Egypt. Afterward he will let you go from here. When he lets
        you go, he will surely drive you out of here altogether. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Speak now in the hearing of the people, and let every man ask from
        his neighbor and every woman from her neighbor, articles of silver and articles
        of gold.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the Lord gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians.
        Moreover the man Moses was very great in the land of Egypt, in the sight
        of Pharaoh\u2019s servants and in the sight of the people."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018About midnight I
        will go out into the midst of Egypt; "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and all the firstborn in the land of Egypt shall die, from the firstborn
        of Pharaoh who sits on his throne, even to the firstborn of the female servant
        who is behind the handmill, and all the firstborn of the animals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then there shall be a great cry throughout all the land of Egypt,
        such as was not like it before, nor shall be like it again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But against none of the children of Israel shall a dog move its tongue,
        against man or beast, that you may know that the Lord does make a difference
        between the Egyptians and Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And all these your servants shall come down to me and bow down to
        me, saying, \u2018Get out, and all the people who follow you!\u2019 After
        that I will go out.\u201D Then he went out from Pharaoh in great anger."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the Lord said to Moses, \u201CPharaoh will not heed you, so that
        My wonders may be multiplied in the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Moses and Aaron did all these wonders before Pharaoh; and the
        Lord hardened Pharaoh\u2019s heart, and he did not let the children of Israel
        go out of his land."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Passover Instituted'
      title: The Passover Instituted
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis month shall  be your beginning of months; it shall  be
        the first month of the year to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Speak to all the congregation of Israel, saying: \u2018On the tenth
        of this month every man shall take for himself a lamb, according to the house
        of his father, a lamb for a household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And if the household is too small for the lamb, let him and his neighbor
        next to his house take it according to the number of the persons; according
        to each man\u2019s need you shall make your count for the lamb. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your lamb shall be without blemish, a male of the first year. You
        may take it from the sheep or from the goats. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now you shall keep it until the fourteenth day of the same month.
        Then the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel shall kill it at twilight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they shall take some of the blood and put it on the two doorposts
        and on the lintel of the houses where they eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then they shall eat the flesh on that night; roasted in fire, with
        unleavened bread and with bitter herbs they shall eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Do not eat it raw, nor boiled at all with water, but roasted in fire\u2014its
        head with its legs and its entrails. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall let none of it remain until morning, and what remains of
        it until morning you shall burn with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And thus you shall eat it: with a belt on your waist, your sandals
        on your feet, and your staff in your hand. So you shall eat it in haste.
        It is the Lord\u2019s Passover."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u2018For I will pass through the land of Egypt on that night, and
        will strike all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both man and beast; and
        against all the gods of Egypt I will execute judgment: I am the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Now the blood shall be a sign for you on the houses where you are.
        And when I see the blood, I will pass over you; and the plague shall not
        be on you to destroy you when I strike the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018So this day shall be to you a memorial; and you shall keep
        it as a feast to the Lord throughout your generations. You shall keep it
        as a feast by an everlasting ordinance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread. On the first day you shall
        remove leaven from your houses. For whoever eats leavened bread from the
        first day until the seventh day, that person shall be cut off from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "On the first day there  shall  be  a holy convocation, and on the
        seventh day there shall be a holy convocation for you. No manner of work
        shall be done on them; but that which everyone must eat\u2014that only may
        be prepared by you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So you shall observe the  Feast  of Unleavened Bread, for on this
        same day I will have brought your armies out of the land of Egypt. Therefore
        you shall observe this day throughout your generations as an everlasting
        ordinance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month at evening,
        you shall eat unleavened bread, until the twenty-first day of the month at
        evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For seven days no leaven shall be found in your houses, since whoever
        eats what is leavened, that same person shall be cut off from the congregation
        of Israel, whether he  is a stranger or a native of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You shall eat nothing leavened; in all your dwellings you shall eat
        unleavened bread.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Moses called for all the elders of Israel and said to them,
        \u201CPick out and take lambs for yourselves according to your families,
        and kill the Passover lamb.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you shall take a bunch of hyssop, dip it in the blood that is
        in the basin, and strike the lintel and the two doorposts with the blood
        that is in the basin. And none of you shall go out of the door of his house
        until morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the Lord will pass through to strike the Egyptians; and when
        He sees the blood on the lintel and on the two doorposts, the Lord will pass
        over the door and not allow the destroyer to come into your houses to strike
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And you shall observe this thing as an ordinance for you and your
        sons forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It will come to pass when you come to the land which the Lord will
        give you, just as He promised, that you shall keep this service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And it shall be, when your children say to you, \u2018What do you
        mean by this service?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "that you shall say, \u2018It is the Passover sacrifice of the Lord,
        who passed over the houses of the children of Israel in Egypt when He struck
        the Egyptians and delivered our households.\u2019 \u201D So the people bowed
        their heads and worshiped. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Tenth Plague: Death of the Firstborn'
      title: 'The Tenth Plague: Death of the Firstborn'
      number: 28
      content: Then the children of Israel went away and did so; just as the Lord
        had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And it came to pass at midnight that the Lord struck all the firstborn
        in the land of Egypt, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sat on his throne
        to the firstborn of the captive who was in the dungeon, and all the firstborn
        of livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Exodus'
      title: The Exodus
      number: 30
      content: So Pharaoh rose in the night, he, all his servants, and all the Egyptians;
        and there was a great cry in Egypt, for there  was not a house where there 
        was not one dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he called for Moses and Aaron by night, and said, \u201CRise,
        go out from among my people, both you and the children of Israel. And go,
        serve the Lord as you have said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Also take your flocks and your herds, as you have said, and be gone;
        and bless me also.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the Egyptians urged the people, that they might send them out
        of the land in haste. For they said, \u201CWe shall all be dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So the people took their dough before it was leavened, having their
        kneading bowls bound up in their clothes on their shoulders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Now the children of Israel had done according to the word of Moses,
        and they had asked from the Egyptians articles of silver, articles of gold,
        and clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: And the Lord had given the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians,
        so that they granted them what  they  requested. Thus they plundered the
        Egyptians.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then the children of Israel journeyed from Rameses to Succoth, about
        six hundred thousand men on foot, besides children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "A mixed multitude went up with them also, and flocks and herds\u2014a
        great deal of livestock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: And they baked unleavened cakes of the dough which they had brought
        out of Egypt; for it was not leavened, because they were driven out of Egypt
        and could not wait, nor had they prepared provisions for themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Now the sojourn of the children of Israel who lived in Egypt was 
        four hundred and thirty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And it came to pass at the end of the four hundred and thirty years\u2014on
        that very same day\u2014it came to pass that all the armies of the Lord went
        out from the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: Passover Regulations'
      title: Passover Regulations
      number: 42
      content: It is  a night of solemn observance to the Lord for bringing them
        out of the land of Egypt. This is that night of the Lord, a solemn observance
        for all the children of Israel throughout their generations.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, \u201CThis is  the ordinance
        of the Passover: No foreigner shall eat it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "But every man\u2019s servant who is bought for money, when you have
        circumcised him, then he may eat it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'A sojourner and a hired servant shall not eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'In one house it shall be eaten; you shall not carry any of the flesh
        outside the house, nor shall you break one of its bones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'All the congregation of Israel shall keep it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And when a stranger dwells with you and  wants to keep the Passover
        to the Lord, let all his males be circumcised, and then let him come near
        and keep it; and he shall be as a native of the land. For no uncircumcised
        person shall eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "One law shall be for the native-born and for the stranger who dwells
        among you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Thus all the children of Israel did; as the Lord commanded Moses
        and Aaron, so they did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: And it came to pass, on that very same day, that the Lord brought
        the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt according to their armies.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: ': '
      title: 
      number: 
      content: 
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Red Sea Crossing'
      title: The Red Sea Crossing
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Lord spoke to Moses, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak to the children of Israel, that they turn and camp before
        Pi Hahiroth, between Migdol and the sea, opposite Baal Zephon; you shall
        camp before it by the sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For Pharaoh will say of the children of Israel, \u2018They are bewildered
        by the land; the wilderness has closed them in.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I will harden Pharaoh\u2019s heart, so that he will pursue them;
        and I will gain honor over Pharaoh and over all his army, that the Egyptians
        may know that I am the Lord.\u201D And they did so."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now it was told the king of Egypt that the people had fled, and the
        heart of Pharaoh and his servants was turned against the people; and they
        said, \u201CWhy have we done this, that we have let Israel go from serving
        us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So he made ready his chariot and took his people with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also, he took six hundred choice chariots, and all the chariots of
        Egypt with captains over every one of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Lord  hardened the heart of Pharaoh king of Egypt, and he
        pursued the children of Israel; and the children of Israel went out with
        boldness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So the Egyptians pursued them, all the horses and chariots of Pharaoh,
        his horsemen and his army, and overtook them camping by the sea beside Pi
        Hahiroth, before Baal Zephon.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And when Pharaoh drew near, the children of Israel lifted their eyes,
        and behold, the Egyptians marched after them. So they were very afraid, and
        the children of Israel cried out to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then they said to Moses, \u201CBecause there  were no graves in Egypt,
        have you taken us away to die in the wilderness? Why have you so dealt with
        us, to bring us up out of Egypt? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Is this not the word that we told you in Egypt, saying, \u2018Let
        us alone that we may serve the Egyptians\u2019? For it  would  have  been
        better for us to serve the Egyptians than that we should die in the wilderness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Moses said to the people, \u201CDo not be afraid. Stand still,
        and see the salvation of the Lord, which He will accomplish for you today.
        For the Egyptians whom you see today, you shall see again no more forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord will fight for you, and you shall hold your peace.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWhy do you cry to Me? Tell the
        children of Israel to go forward. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But lift up your rod, and stretch out your hand over the sea and
        divide it. And the children of Israel shall go on dry ground through the
        midst of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I indeed will harden the hearts of the Egyptians, and they shall
        follow them. So I will gain honor over Pharaoh and over all his army, his
        chariots, and his horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the Egyptians shall know that I am the Lord, when I have gained
        honor for Myself over Pharaoh, his chariots, and his horsemen.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the Angel of God, who went before the camp of Israel, moved and
        went behind them; and the pillar of cloud went from before them and stood
        behind them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So it came between the camp of the Egyptians and the camp of Israel.
        Thus it was a cloud and darkness to  the  one, and it gave light by night
        to  the  other, so that the one did not come near the other all that night.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Moses stretched out his hand over the sea; and the Lord caused
        the sea to go back by a strong east wind all that night, and made the sea
        into dry land, and the waters were divided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the children of Israel went into the midst of the sea on the dry
        ground, and the waters were  a wall to them on their right hand and on their
        left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the Egyptians pursued and went after them into the midst of the
        sea, all Pharaoh\u2019s horses, his chariots, and his horsemen."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now it came to pass, in the morning watch, that the Lord looked down
        upon the army of the Egyptians through the pillar of fire and cloud, and
        He troubled the army of the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And He took off their chariot wheels, so that they drove them with
        difficulty; and the Egyptians said, \u201CLet us flee from the face of Israel,
        for the Lord  fights for them against the Egyptians.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand over the
        sea, that the waters may come back upon the Egyptians, on their chariots,
        and on their horsemen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Moses stretched out his hand over the sea; and when the morning
        appeared, the sea returned to its full depth, while the Egyptians were fleeing
        into it. So the Lord  overthrew the Egyptians in the midst of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then the waters returned and covered the chariots, the horsemen,
        and all the army of Pharaoh that came into the sea after them. Not so much
        as one of them remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: But the children of Israel had walked on dry land in the midst of
        the sea, and the waters were a wall to them on their right hand and on their
        left.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So the Lord  saved Israel that day out of the hand of the Egyptians,
        and Israel saw the Egyptians dead on the seashore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Thus Israel saw the great work which the Lord had done in Egypt; so
        the people feared the Lord, and believed the Lord and His servant Moses.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Moses'
      title: The Song of Moses
      number: 1
      content: "Then Moses and the children of Israel sang this song to the Lord,
        and spoke, saying:\u201CI will sing to the Lord,For He has triumphed gloriously!The
        horse and its riderHe has thrown into the sea!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord  is my strength and song,And He has become my salvation;He
        is my God, and I will praise Him;My father\u2019s God, and I will exalt Him."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The Lord  is a man of war;The Lord  is His name.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Pharaoh\u2019s chariots and his army He has cast into the sea;His
        chosen captains also are drowned in the Red Sea."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The depths have covered them;They sank to the bottom like a stone.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYour right hand, O Lord, has become glorious in power;Your
        right hand, O Lord, has dashed the enemy in pieces."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And in the greatness of Your excellenceYou have overthrown those who
        rose against You;You sent forth Your wrath;It consumed them like stubble.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And with the blast of Your nostrilsThe waters were gathered together;The
        floods stood upright like a heap;The depths congealed in the heart of the
        sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The enemy said, \u2018I will pursue,I will overtake,I will divide
        the spoil;My desire shall be satisfied on them.I will draw my sword,My hand
        shall destroy them.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: You blew with Your wind,The sea covered them;They sank like lead in
        the mighty waters.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWho is like You, O Lord, among the gods?Who is like You, glorious
        in holiness,Fearful in praises, doing wonders?"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: You stretched out Your right hand;The earth swallowed them.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: You in Your mercy have led forthThe people whom You have redeemed;You
        have guided them in Your strengthTo Your holy habitation.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThe people will hear and be afraid;Sorrow will take hold of
        the inhabitants of Philistia."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then the chiefs of Edom will be dismayed;The mighty men of Moab,Trembling
        will take hold of them;All the inhabitants of Canaan will melt away.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Fear and dread will fall on them;By the greatness of Your armThey
        will be as still as a stone,Till Your people pass over, O Lord,Till the people
        pass overWhom You have purchased.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: You will bring them in and plant themIn the mountain of Your inheritance,In
        the place, O Lord, which You have madeFor Your own dwelling,The sanctuary,
        O Lord, which Your hands have established.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThe  Lord shall reign forever and ever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Song of Miriam'
      title: The Song of Miriam
      number: 19
      content: For the horses of Pharaoh went with his chariots and his horsemen
        into the sea, and the Lord brought back the waters of the sea upon them.
        But the children of Israel went on dry land in the midst of the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Miriam the prophetess, the sister of Aaron, took the timbrel
        in her hand; and all the women went out after her with timbrels and with
        dances. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Bitter Waters Made Sweet'
      title: Bitter Waters Made Sweet
      number: 21
      content: "And Miriam answered them:\u201CSing to the Lord,For He has triumphed
        gloriously!The horse and its riderHe has thrown into the sea!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Moses brought Israel from the Red Sea; then they went out into
        the Wilderness of Shur. And they went three days in the wilderness and found
        no water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now when they came to Marah, they could not drink the waters of Marah,
        for they were bitter. Therefore the name of it was called Marah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the people complained against Moses, saying, \u201CWhat shall
        we drink?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So he cried out to the Lord, and the Lord showed him a tree. When
        he cast it into the waters, the waters were made sweet.There He made a statute
        and an ordinance for them, and there He tested them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and said, \u201CIf you diligently heed the voice of the Lord your
        God and do what is right in His sight, give ear to His commandments and keep
        all His statutes, I will put none of the diseases on you which I have brought
        on the Egyptians. For I am the Lord  who heals you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then they came to Elim, where there were twelve wells of water and
        seventy palm trees; so they camped there by the waters.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bread from Heaven'
      title: Bread from Heaven
      number: 1
      content: 'And they journeyed from Elim, and all the congregation of the children
        of Israel came to the Wilderness of Sin, which is between Elim and Sinai,
        on the fifteenth day of the second month after they departed from the land
        of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the whole congregation of the children of Israel complained
        against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the children of Israel said to them, \u201COh, that we had died
        by the hand of the Lord in the land of Egypt, when we sat by the pots of
        meat and when we ate bread to the full! For you have brought us out into
        this wilderness to kill this whole assembly with hunger.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CBehold, I will rain bread from
        heaven for you. And the people shall go out and gather a certain quota every
        day, that I may test them, whether they will walk in My law or not. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And it shall be on the sixth day that they shall prepare what they
        bring in, and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Moses and Aaron said to all the children of Israel, \u201CAt
        evening you shall know that the Lord has brought you out of the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And in the morning you shall see the glory of the Lord; for He hears
        your complaints against the Lord. But what are we, that you complain against
        us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also Moses said, \u201CThis  shall  be  seen when the Lord gives
        you meat to eat in the evening, and in the morning bread to the full; for
        the Lord hears your complaints which you make against Him. And what are we?
        Your complaints are not against us but against the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Moses spoke to Aaron, \u201CSay to all the congregation of the
        children of Israel, \u2018Come near before the Lord, for He has heard your
        complaints.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Now it came to pass, as Aaron spoke to the whole congregation of the
        children of Israel, that they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the
        glory of the Lord  appeared in the cloud.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI have heard the complaints of the children of Israel. Speak
        to them, saying, \u2018At twilight you shall eat meat, and in the morning
        you shall be filled with bread. And you shall know that I am the Lord your
        God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So it was that quails came up at evening and covered the camp, and
        in the morning the dew lay all around the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when the layer of dew lifted, there, on the surface of the wilderness,
        was a small round substance, as fine as frost on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So when the children of Israel saw it, they said to one another,
        \u201CWhat is it?\u201D For they did not know what it was.And Moses said
        to them, \u201CThis is the bread which the Lord has given you to eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This is the thing which the Lord has commanded: \u2018Let every man
        gather it according to each one\u2019s need, one omer for each person, according 
        to  the number of persons; let every man take for those who are in his tent.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the children of Israel did so and gathered, some more, some
        less. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So when they measured it by omers, he who gathered much had nothing
        left over, and he who gathered little had no lack. Every man had gathered
        according to each one\u2019s need. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Moses said, \u201CLet no one leave any of it till morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Notwithstanding they did not heed Moses. But some of them left part
        of it until morning, and it bred worms and stank. And Moses was angry with
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: So they gathered it every morning, every man according to his need.
        And when the sun became hot, it melted.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And so it was, on the sixth day, that they gathered twice as much
        bread, two omers for each one. And all the rulers of the congregation came
        and told Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CThis is  what the Lord has said: \u2018Tomorrow
        is  a Sabbath rest, a holy Sabbath to the Lord. Bake what you will bake today,
        and boil what you will boil; and lay up for yourselves all that remains,
        to be kept until morning.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So they laid it up till morning, as Moses commanded; and it did not
        stink, nor were there any worms in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CEat that today, for today is a Sabbath to
        the Lord; today you will not find it in the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Six days you shall gather it, but on the seventh day, the Sabbath,
        there will be none.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now it happened that  some of the people went out on the seventh
        day to gather, but they found none. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CHow long do you refuse to keep
        My commandments and My laws? "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "See! For the Lord has given you the Sabbath; therefore He gives you
        on the sixth day bread for two days. Let every man remain in his place; let
        no man go out of his place on the seventh day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: So the people rested on the seventh day.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And the house of Israel called its name Manna. And it was like white
        coriander seed, and the taste of it was like wafers made with honey.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CThis is the thing which the Lord has commanded:
        \u2018Fill an omer with it, to be kept for your generations, that they may
        see the bread with which I fed you in the wilderness, when I brought you
        out of the land of Egypt.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And Moses said to Aaron, \u201CTake a pot and put an omer of manna
        in it, and lay it up before the Lord, to be kept for your generations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'As the Lord commanded Moses, so Aaron laid it up before the Testimony,
        to be kept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the children of Israel ate manna forty years, until they came
        to an inhabited land; they ate manna until they came to the border of the
        land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Now an omer is one-tenth of an ephah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Water from the Rock'
      title: Water from the Rock
      number: 1
      content: 'Then all the congregation of the children of Israel set out on their
        journey from the Wilderness of Sin, according to the commandment of the Lord,
        and camped in Rephidim; but there  was no water for the people to drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore the people contended with Moses, and said, \u201CGive us
        water, that we may drink.\u201DSo Moses said to them, \u201CWhy do you contend
        with me? Why do you tempt the Lord?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the people thirsted there for water, and the people complained
        against Moses, and said, \u201CWhy is it you have brought us up out of Egypt,
        to kill us and our children and our livestock with thirst?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Moses cried out to the Lord, saying, \u201CWhat shall I do with
        this people? They are almost ready to stone me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo on before the people, and take
        with you some of the elders of Israel. Also take in your hand your rod with
        which you struck the river, and go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Behold, I will stand before you there on the rock in Horeb; and you
        shall strike the rock, and water will come out of it, that the people may
        drink.\u201DAnd Moses did so in the sight of the elders of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Victory over the Amalekites'
      title: Victory over the Amalekites
      number: 7
      content: "So he called the name of the place Massah and Meribah, because of
        the contention of the children of Israel, and because they tempted the Lord,
        saying, \u201CIs the Lord among us or not?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now Amalek came and fought with Israel in Rephidim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Moses said to Joshua, \u201CChoose us some men and go out, fight
        with Amalek. Tomorrow I will stand on the top of the hill with the rod of
        God in my hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Joshua did as Moses said to him, and fought with Amalek. And Moses,
        Aaron, and Hur went up to the top of the hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And so it was, when Moses held up his hand, that Israel prevailed;
        and when he let down his hand, Amalek prevailed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Moses\u2019 hands became heavy; so they took a stone and put
        it under him, and he sat on it. And Aaron and Hur supported his hands, one
        on one side, and the other on the other side; and his hands were steady until
        the going down of the sun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So Joshua defeated Amalek and his people with the edge of the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWrite this for a memorial in the
        book and recount it in the hearing of Joshua, that I will utterly blot out
        the remembrance of Amalek from under heaven.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Moses built an altar and called its name, The-Lord-Is-My-Banner; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "for he said, \u201CBecause the Lord has sworn: the Lord  will  have
        war with Amalek from generation to generation.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jethro\u2019s Advice"
      title: "Jethro\u2019s Advice"
      number: 1
      content: "And Jethro, the priest of Midian, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, heard
        of all that God had done for Moses and for Israel His people\u2014that the
        Lord had brought Israel out of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jethro, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, took Zipporah, Moses\u2019
        wife, after he had sent her back, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "with her two sons, of whom the name of one was Gershom (for he said,
        \u201CI have been a stranger in a foreign land\u201D) "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and the name of the other was Eliezer (for he  said, \u201CThe God
        of my father was my help, and delivered me from the sword of Pharaoh\u201D); "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and Jethro, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, came with his sons and his
        wife to Moses in the wilderness, where he was encamped at the mountain of
        God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now he had said to Moses, \u201CI, your father-in-law Jethro, am
        coming to you with your wife and her two sons with her.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Moses went out to meet his father-in-law, bowed down, and kissed
        him. And they asked each other about their well-being, and they went into
        the tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Moses told his father-in-law all that the Lord had done to Pharaoh
        and to the Egyptians for Israel\u2019s sake, all the hardship that had come
        upon them on the way, and how the Lord had delivered them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jethro rejoiced for all the good which the Lord had done for
        Israel, whom He had delivered out of the hand of the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Jethro said, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, who has delivered you
        out of the hand of the Egyptians and out of the hand of Pharaoh, and who
        has delivered the people from under the hand of the Egyptians. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now I know that the Lord  is  greater than all the gods; for in the
        very thing in which they behaved proudly, He  was above them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jethro, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, took a burnt offering and
        other sacrifices to  offer to God. And Aaron came with all the elders of
        Israel to eat bread with Moses\u2019 father-in-law before God."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And so it was, on the next day, that Moses sat to judge the people;
        and the people stood before Moses from morning until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So when Moses\u2019 father-in-law saw all that he did for the people,
        he said, \u201CWhat is this thing that you are doing for the people? Why
        do you alone sit, and all the people stand before you from morning until
        evening?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Moses said to his father-in-law, \u201CBecause the people come
        to me to inquire of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When they have a difficulty, they come to me, and I judge between
        one and another; and I make known the statutes of God and His laws.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Moses\u2019 father-in-law said to him, \u201CThe thing that you
        do is not good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Both you and these people who are with you will surely wear yourselves
        out. For this thing is too much for you; you are not able to perform it by
        yourself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Listen now to my voice; I will give you counsel, and God will be
        with you: Stand before God for the people, so that you may bring the difficulties
        to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And you shall teach them the statutes and the laws, and show them
        the way in which they must walk and the work they must do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Moreover you shall select from all the people able men, such as fear
        God, men of truth, hating covetousness; and place such over them to  be rulers
        of thousands, rulers of hundreds, rulers of fifties, and rulers of tens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And let them judge the people at all times. Then it will be that
        every great matter they shall bring to you, but every small matter they themselves
        shall judge. So it will be easier for you, for they will bear the  burden
        with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "If you do this thing, and God so commands you, then you will be able
        to endure, and all this people will also go to their place in peace.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Moses heeded the voice of his father-in-law and did all that he
        had said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Moses chose able men out of all Israel, and made them heads over
        the people: rulers of thousands, rulers of hundreds, rulers of fifties, and
        rulers of tens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So they judged the people at all times; the hard cases they brought
        to Moses, but they judged every small case themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then Moses let his father-in-law depart, and he went his way to his
        own land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel at Mount Sinai'
      title: Israel at Mount Sinai
      number: 1
      content: 'In the third month after the children of Israel had gone out of the
        land of Egypt, on the same day, they came to the Wilderness of Sinai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For they had departed from Rephidim, had come to the Wilderness of
        Sinai, and camped in the wilderness. So Israel camped there before the mountain.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Moses went up to God, and the Lord  called to him from the mountain,
        saying, \u201CThus you shall say to the house of Jacob, and tell the children
        of Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018You have seen what I did to the Egyptians, and how  I bore
        you on eagles\u2019 wings and brought you to Myself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now therefore, if you will indeed obey My voice and keep My covenant,
        then you shall be a special treasure to Me above all people; for all the
        earth is  Mine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And you shall be to Me a kingdom of priests and a holy nation.\u2019
        These are the words which you shall speak to the children of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Moses came and called for the elders of the people, and laid before
        them all these words which the Lord commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then all the people answered together and said, \u201CAll that the
        Lord has spoken we will do.\u201D So Moses brought back the words of the
        people to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CBehold, I come to you in the thick
        cloud, that the people may hear when I speak with you, and believe you forever.\u201DSo
        Moses told the words of the people to the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo to the people and consecrate
        them today and tomorrow, and let them wash their clothes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And let them be ready for the third day. For on the third day the
        Lord will come down upon Mount Sinai in the sight of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You shall set bounds for the people all around, saying, \u2018Take
        heed to yourselves that you do not go up to the mountain or touch its base.
        Whoever touches the mountain shall surely be put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Not a hand shall touch him, but he shall surely be stoned or shot
        with  an  arrow; whether man or beast, he shall not live.\u2019 When the
        trumpet sounds long, they shall come near the mountain.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Moses went down from the mountain to the people and sanctified
        the people, and they washed their clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said to the people, \u201CBe ready for the third day; do not
        come near your wives.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then it came to pass on the third day, in the morning, that there
        were thunderings and lightnings, and a thick cloud on the mountain; and the
        sound of the trumpet was very loud, so that all the people who were in the
        camp trembled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Moses brought the people out of the camp to meet with God, and
        they stood at the foot of the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Mount Sinai was completely in smoke, because the Lord descended
        upon it in fire. Its smoke ascended like the smoke of a furnace, and the
        whole mountain quaked greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And when the blast of the trumpet sounded long and became louder
        and louder, Moses spoke, and God answered him by voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Then the Lord came down upon Mount Sinai, on the top of the mountain.
        And the Lord called Moses to the top of the mountain, and Moses went up.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo down and warn the people, lest
        they break through to gaze at the Lord, and many of them perish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Also let the priests who come near the Lord  consecrate themselves,
        lest the Lord  break out against them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But Moses said to the Lord, \u201CThe people cannot come up to Mount
        Sinai; for You warned us, saying, \u2018Set bounds around the mountain and
        consecrate it.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the Lord said to him, \u201CAway! Get down and then come up,
        you and Aaron with you. But do not let the priests and the people break through
        to come up to the Lord, lest He break out against them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So Moses went down to the people and spoke to them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ten Commandments'
      title: The Ten Commandments
      number: 1
      content: 'And God spoke all these words, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI am the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of
        Egypt, out of the house of bondage."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou shall have no other gods before Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou shall not make for yourself a carved image\u2014any likeness
        of  anything that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth beneath, or
        that is in the water under the earth; "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'you shall not bow down to them nor serve them. For I, the Lord your
        God, am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children
        to the third and fourth generations of those who hate Me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: but showing mercy to thousands, to those who love Me and keep My commandments.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou shall not take the name of the Lord your God in vain, for
        the Lord  will not hold him guiltless who takes His name in vain."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CRemember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Six days you shall labor and do all your work, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but the seventh day is the Sabbath of the Lord your God. In  it you
        shall do no work: you, nor your son, nor your daughter, nor your male servant,
        nor your female servant, nor your cattle, nor your stranger who is within
        your gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For in six days the Lord made the heavens and the earth, the sea,
        and all that is in them, and rested the seventh day. Therefore the Lord blessed
        the Sabbath day and hallowed it.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHonor your father and your mother, that your days may be long
        upon the land which the Lord your God is giving you."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall not murder."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall not commit adultery."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CYou shall not steal."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CYou shall not bear false witness against your neighbor."
      comments: []
    - name: "17: The People Afraid of God\u2019s Presence"
      title: "The People Afraid of God\u2019s Presence"
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou shall not covet your neighbor\u2019s house; you shall not
        covet your neighbor\u2019s wife, nor his male servant, nor his female servant,
        nor his ox, nor his donkey, nor anything that is your neighbor\u2019s.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now all the people witnessed the thunderings, the lightning flashes,
        the sound of the trumpet, and the mountain smoking; and when the people saw
        it, they trembled and stood afar off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then they said to Moses, \u201CYou speak with us, and we will hear;
        but let not God speak with us, lest we die.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Moses said to the people, \u201CDo not fear; for God has come
        to test you, and that His fear may be before you, so that you may not sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Law of the Altar'
      title: The Law of the Altar
      number: 21
      content: So the people stood afar off, but Moses drew near the thick darkness
        where God was.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CThus you shall say to the children
        of Israel: \u2018You have seen that I have talked with you from heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "You shall not make anything  to  be  with Me\u2014gods of silver
        or gods of gold you shall not make for yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'An altar of earth you shall make for Me, and you shall sacrifice
        on it your burnt offerings and your peace offerings, your sheep and your
        oxen. In every place where I record My name I will come to you, and I will
        bless you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And if you make Me an altar of stone, you shall not build it of hewn
        stone; for if you use your tool on it, you have profaned it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Nor shall you go up by steps to My altar, that your nakedness may
        not be exposed on it.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Law Concerning Servants'
      title: The Law Concerning Servants
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CNow these are the judgments which you shall set before them: "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'If you buy a Hebrew servant, he shall serve six years; and in the
        seventh he shall go out free and pay nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If he comes in by himself, he shall go out by himself; if he comes 
        in married, then his wife shall go out with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "If his master has given him a wife, and she has borne him sons or
        daughters, the wife and her children shall be her master\u2019s, and he shall
        go out by himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if the servant plainly says, \u2018I love my master, my wife,
        and my children; I will not go out free,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: then his master shall bring him to the judges. He shall also bring
        him to the door, or to the doorpost, and his master shall pierce his ear
        with an awl; and he shall serve him forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man sells his daughter to be a female slave, she shall
        not go out as the male slaves do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'If she does not please her master, who has betrothed her to himself,
        then he shall let her be redeemed. He shall have no right to sell her to
        a foreign people, since he has dealt deceitfully with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And if he has betrothed her to his son, he shall deal with her according
        to the custom of daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If he takes another wife, he shall not diminish her food, her clothing,
        and her marriage rights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Law Concerning Violence'
      title: The Law Concerning Violence
      number: 11
      content: And if he does not do these three for her, then she shall go out free,
        without paying money.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHe who strikes a man so that he dies shall surely be put to
        death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: However, if he did not lie in wait, but God delivered him into his
        hand, then I will appoint for you a place where he may flee.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBut if a man acts with premeditation against his neighbor,
        to kill him by treachery, you shall take him from My altar, that he may die."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd he who strikes his father or his mother shall surely be
        put to death."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CHe who kidnaps a man and sells him, or if he is found in his
        hand, shall surely be put to death."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnd he who curses his father or his mother shall surely be
        put to death."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf men contend with each other, and one strikes the other with
        a stone or with his fist, and he does not die but is confined to his bed, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: if he rises again and walks about outside with his staff, then he
        who struck him shall be acquitted. He shall only pay for the loss of his
        time, and shall provide for  him to be thoroughly healed.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man beats his male or female servant with a rod, so
        that he dies under his hand, he shall surely be punished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Notwithstanding, if he remains alive a day or two, he shall not be
        punished; for he is his property.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf men fight, and hurt a woman with child, so that she gives
        birth prematurely, yet no harm follows, he shall surely be punished accordingly
        as the woman\u2019s husband imposes on him; and he shall pay as the judges
        determine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But if any harm follows, then you shall give life for life, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: burn for burn, wound for wound, stripe for stripe.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CIf a man strikes the eye of his male or female servant, and
        destroys it, he shall let him go free for the sake of his eye. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Animal Control Laws'
      title: Animal Control Laws
      number: 27
      content: And if he knocks out the tooth of his male or female servant, he shall
        let him go free for the sake of his tooth.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIf an ox gores a man or a woman to death, then the ox shall
        surely be stoned, and its flesh shall not be eaten; but the owner of the
        ox shall  be acquitted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But if the ox tended to thrust with its horn in times past, and it
        has been made known to his owner, and he has not kept it confined, so that
        it has killed a man or a woman, the ox shall be stoned and its owner also
        shall be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'If there is imposed on him a sum of money, then he shall pay to redeem
        his life, whatever is imposed on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Whether it has gored a son or gored a daughter, according to this
        judgment it shall be done to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: If the ox gores a male or female servant, he shall give to their master
        thirty shekels of silver, and the ox shall be stoned.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man opens a pit, or if a man digs a pit and does not
        cover it, and an ox or a donkey falls in it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: the owner of the pit shall make it good; he shall give money to their
        owner, but the dead animal shall be his.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CIf one man\u2019s ox hurts another\u2019s, so that it dies,
        then they shall sell the live ox and divide the money from it; and the dead
        ox they shall also divide. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Or if it was known that the ox tended to thrust in time past, and
        its owner has not kept it confined, he shall surely pay ox for ox, and the
        dead animal shall be his own.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Responsibility for Property'
      title: Responsibility for Property
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CIf a man steals an ox or a sheep, and slaughters it or sells
        it, he shall restore five oxen for an ox and four sheep for a sheep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'If the thief is found breaking in, and he is struck so that he dies,
        there  shall  be  no guilt for his bloodshed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If the sun has risen on him, there  shall  be guilt for his bloodshed.
        He should make full restitution; if he has nothing, then he shall be sold
        for his theft. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: If the theft is certainly found alive in his hand, whether it is an
        ox or donkey or sheep, he shall restore double.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf a man causes a field or vineyard to be grazed, and lets
        loose his animal, and it feeds in another man\u2019s field, he shall make
        restitution from the best of his own field and the best of his own vineyard."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf fire breaks out and catches in thorns, so that stacked grain,
        standing grain, or the field is consumed, he who kindled the fire shall surely
        make restitution."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf a man delivers to his neighbor money or articles to keep,
        and it is stolen out of the man\u2019s house, if the thief is found, he shall
        pay double. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If the thief is not found, then the master of the house shall be
        brought to the judges to  see whether he has put his hand into his neighbor\u2019s
        goods."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor any kind of trespass, whether  it  concerns an ox, a donkey,
        a sheep, or clothing, or for any kind of lost thing which another claims
        to be his, the cause of both parties shall come before the judges; and whomever
        the judges condemn shall pay double to his neighbor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If a man delivers to his neighbor a donkey, an ox, a sheep, or any
        animal to keep, and it dies, is hurt, or driven away, no one seeing it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "then an oath of the Lord shall be between them both, that he has
        not put his hand into his neighbor\u2019s goods; and the owner of it shall
        accept that, and he shall not make it good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But if, in fact, it is stolen from him, he shall make restitution
        to the owner of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: If it is torn to pieces by  a  beast, then he shall bring it as evidence,
        and he shall not make good what was torn.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man borrows anything from his neighbor, and it becomes
        injured or dies, the owner of it not being with it, he shall surely make
        it good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Moral and Ceremonial Principles'
      title: Moral and Ceremonial Principles
      number: 15
      content: If its owner was with it, he shall not make it good; if it was hired,
        it came for its hire.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf a man entices a virgin who is not betrothed, and lies with
        her, he shall surely pay the bride-price for her to  be his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: If her father utterly refuses to give her to him, he shall pay money
        according to the bride-price of virgins.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall not permit a sorceress to live."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhoever lies with an animal shall surely be put to death."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CHe who sacrifices to any god, except to the Lord only, he shall
        be utterly destroyed."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou shall neither mistreat a stranger nor oppress him, for
        you were strangers in the land of Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYou shall not afflict any widow or fatherless child. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If you afflict them in any way, and they cry at all to Me, I will
        surely hear their cry; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: and My wrath will become hot, and I will kill you with the sword;
        your wives shall be widows, and your children fatherless.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CIf you lend money to any  of My people who  are poor among
        you, you shall not be like a moneylender to him; you shall not charge him
        interest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "If you ever take your neighbor\u2019s garment as a pledge, you shall
        return it to him before the sun goes down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For that is his only covering, it is his garment for his skin. What
        will he sleep in? And it will be that when he cries to Me, I will hear, for
        I am  gracious.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CYou shall not revile God, nor curse a ruler of your people."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CYou shall not delay to  offer  the first of your ripe produce
        and your juices. The firstborn of your sons you shall give to Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Likewise you shall do with your oxen and your sheep. It shall be with
        its mother seven days; on the eighth day you shall give it to Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall be holy men to Me: you shall not eat meat torn
        by  beasts in the field; you shall throw it to the dogs."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Justice for All'
      title: Justice for All
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CYou shall not circulate a false report. Do not put your hand
        with the wicked to be an unrighteous witness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall not follow a crowd to do evil; nor shall you testify in
        a dispute so as to turn aside after many to pervert justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You shall not show partiality to a poor man in his dispute.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIf you meet your enemy\u2019s ox or his donkey going astray,
        you shall surely bring it back to him again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: If you see the donkey of one who hates you lying under its burden,
        and you would refrain from helping it, you shall surely help him with it.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou shall not pervert the judgment of your poor in his dispute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Keep yourself far from a false matter; do not kill the innocent and
        righteous. For I will not justify the wicked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And you shall take no bribe, for a bribe blinds the discerning and
        perverts the words of the righteous.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Law of Sabbaths'
      title: The Law of Sabbaths
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAlso you shall not oppress a stranger, for you know the heart
        of a stranger, because you were strangers in the land of Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CSix years you shall sow your land and gather in its produce, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'but the seventh year you shall let it rest and lie fallow, that the
        poor of your people may eat; and what they leave, the beasts of the field
        may eat. In like manner you shall do with your vineyard and your olive grove. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Six days you shall do your work, and on the seventh day you shall
        rest, that your ox and your donkey may rest, and the son of your female servant
        and the stranger may be refreshed.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Three Annual Feasts'
      title: Three Annual Feasts
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAnd in all that I have said to you, be circumspect and make
        no mention of the name of other gods, nor let it be heard from your mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThree times you shall keep a feast to Me in the year: "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall keep the Feast of Unleavened Bread (you shall eat unleavened
        bread seven days, as I commanded you, at the time appointed in the month
        of Abib, for in it you came out of Egypt; none shall appear before Me empty); '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: and the Feast of Harvest, the firstfruits of your labors which you
        have sown in the field; and the Feast of Ingathering at the end of the year,
        when you have gathered in the  fruit  of your labors from the field.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThree times in the year all your males shall appear before
        the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened
        bread; nor shall the fat of My sacrifice remain until morning. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Angel and the Promises'
      title: The Angel and the Promises
      number: 19
      content: "The first of the firstfruits of your land you shall bring into the
        house of the Lord your God. You shall not boil a young goat in its mother\u2019s
        milk."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBehold, I send an Angel before you to keep you in the way and
        to bring you into the place which I have prepared. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Beware of Him and obey His voice; do not provoke Him, for He will
        not pardon your transgressions; for My name is in Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But if you indeed obey His voice and do all that I speak, then I
        will be an enemy to your enemies and an adversary to your adversaries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For My Angel will go before you and bring you in to the Amorites
        and the Hittites and the Perizzites and the Canaanites and the Hivites and
        the Jebusites; and I will cut them off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: You shall not bow down to their gods, nor serve them, nor do according
        to their works; but you shall utterly overthrow them and completely break
        down their sacred pillars.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CSo you shall serve the Lord your God, and He will bless your
        bread and your water. And I will take sickness away from the midst of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: No one shall suffer miscarriage or be barren in your land; I will
        fulfill the number of your days.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI will send My fear before you, I will cause confusion among
        all the people to whom you come, and will make all your enemies turn their
        backs to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And I will send hornets before you, which shall drive out the Hivite,
        the Canaanite, and the Hittite from before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I will not drive them out from before you in one year, lest the land
        become desolate and the beasts of the field become too numerous for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Little by little I will drive them out from before you, until you
        have increased, and you inherit the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And I will set your bounds from the Red Sea to the sea, Philistia,
        and from the desert to the River. For I will deliver the inhabitants of the
        land into your hand, and you shall drive them out before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You shall make no covenant with them, nor with their gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "They shall not dwell in your land, lest they make you sin against
        Me. For if you serve their gods, it will surely be a snare to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Affirms the Covenant'
      title: Israel Affirms the Covenant
      number: 1
      content: "Now He said to Moses, \u201CCome up to the Lord, you and Aaron, Nadab
        and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel, and worship from afar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Moses alone shall come near the Lord, but they shall not come
        near; nor shall the people go up with him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Moses came and told the people all the words of the Lord and all
        the judgments. And all the people answered with one voice and said, \u201CAll
        the words which the Lord has said we will do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Moses wrote all the words of the Lord. And he rose early in the
        morning, and built an altar at the foot of the mountain, and twelve pillars
        according to the twelve tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then he sent young men of the children of Israel, who offered burnt
        offerings and sacrificed peace offerings of oxen to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Moses took half the blood and put it in basins, and half the
        blood he sprinkled on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he took the Book of the Covenant and read in the hearing of
        the people. And they said, \u201CAll that the Lord has said we will do, and
        be obedient.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: On the Mountain with God'
      title: On the Mountain with God
      number: 8
      content: "And Moses took the blood, sprinkled it on the people, and said, \u201CThis
        is the blood of the covenant which the Lord has made with you according to
        all these words.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Moses went up, also Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and seventy of
        the elders of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and they saw the God of Israel. And there  was under His feet as
        it were a paved work of sapphire stone, and it was like the very heavens
        in its clarity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: But on the nobles of the children of Israel He did not lay His hand.
        So they saw God, and they ate and drank.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CCome up to Me on the mountain
        and be there; and I will give you tablets of stone, and the law and commandments
        which I have written, that you may teach them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Moses arose with his assistant Joshua, and Moses went up to the
        mountain of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said to the elders, \u201CWait here for us until we come back
        to you. Indeed, Aaron and Hur are with you. If any man has a difficulty,
        let him go to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then Moses went up into the mountain, and a cloud covered the mountain.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now the glory of the Lord rested on Mount Sinai, and the cloud covered
        it six days. And on the seventh day He called to Moses out of the midst of
        the cloud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sight of the glory of the Lord  was like a consuming fire on
        the top of the mountain in the eyes of the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: So Moses went into the midst of the cloud and went up into the mountain.
        And Moses was on the mountain forty days and forty nights.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Offerings for the Sanctuary'
      title: Offerings for the Sanctuary
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak to the children of Israel, that they bring Me an offering.
        From everyone who gives it willingly with his heart you shall take My offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And this is the offering which you shall take from them: gold, silver,
        and bronze; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "blue, purple, and scarlet thread, fine linen, and goats\u2019 hair;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'ram skins dyed red, badger skins, and acacia wood; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'oil for the light, and spices for the anointing oil and for the sweet
        incense; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'onyx stones, and stones to be set in the ephod and in the breastplate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And let them make Me a sanctuary, that I may dwell among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Ark of the Testimony'
      title: The Ark of the Testimony
      number: 9
      content: According to all that I show you, that  is, the pattern of the tabernacle
        and the pattern of all its furnishings, just so you shall make it.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd they shall make an ark of acacia wood; two and a half cubits
        shall  be its length, a cubit and a half its width, and a cubit and a half
        its height. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall overlay it with pure gold, inside and out you shall
        overlay it, and shall make on it a molding of gold all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall cast four rings of gold for it, and put them in its four
        corners; two rings shall  be on one side, and two rings on the other side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And you shall make poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark, that
        the ark may be carried by them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The poles shall be in the rings of the ark; they shall not be taken
        from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And you shall put into the ark the Testimony which I will give you.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a mercy seat of pure gold; two and a half cubits
        shall  be its length and a cubit and a half its width. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you shall make two cherubim of gold; of hammered work you shall
        make them at the two ends of the mercy seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Make one cherub at one end, and the other cherub at the other end;
        you shall make the cherubim at the two ends of it of  one  piece with the
        mercy seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the cherubim shall stretch out their wings above, covering the
        mercy seat with their wings, and they shall face one another; the faces of
        the cherubim shall  be toward the mercy seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You shall put the mercy seat on top of the ark, and in the ark you
        shall put the Testimony that I will give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Table for the Showbread'
      title: The Table for the Showbread
      number: 22
      content: And there I will meet with you, and I will speak with you from above
        the mercy seat, from between the two cherubim which are on the ark of the
        Testimony, about everything which I will give you in commandment to the children
        of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make a table of acacia wood; two cubits shall 
        be its length, a cubit its width, and a cubit and a half its height. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And you shall overlay it with pure gold, and make a molding of gold
        all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall make for it a frame of a handbreadth all around, and you
        shall make a gold molding for the frame all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And you shall make for it four rings of gold, and put the rings on
        the four corners that are at its four legs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The rings shall be close to the frame, as holders for the poles to
        bear the table. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And you shall make the poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with
        gold, that the table may be carried with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall make its dishes, its pans, its pitchers, and its bowls
        for pouring. You shall make them of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Gold Lampstand'
      title: The Gold Lampstand
      number: 30
      content: And you shall set the showbread on the table before Me always.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make a lampstand of pure gold; the lampstand
        shall be of hammered work. Its shaft, its branches, its bowls, its ornamental
        knobs, and flowers shall be of  one  piece.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And six branches shall come out of its sides: three branches of the
        lampstand out of one side, and three branches of the lampstand out of the
        other side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Three bowls shall  be made like almond blossoms on one branch, with
        an ornamental knob and a flower, and three bowls made like almond blossoms
        on the other branch, with an ornamental knob and a flower\u2014and so for
        the six branches that come out of the lampstand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'On the lampstand itself four bowls shall  be made like almond blossoms,
        each with its ornamental knob and flower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And there  shall  be a knob under the first two branches of the same,
        a knob under the second two branches of the same, and a knob under the third
        two branches of the same, according to the six branches that extend from
        the lampstand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Their knobs and their branches shall  be  of  one  piece; all of
        it shall  be one hammered piece of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You shall make seven lamps for it, and they shall arrange its lamps
        so that they give light in front of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And its wick-trimmers and their trays shall  be of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'It shall be made of a talent of pure gold, with all these utensils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: And see to it that you make them according to the pattern which was
        shown you on the mountain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tabernacle'
      title: The Tabernacle
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMoreover you shall make the tabernacle with ten curtains of
        fine woven linen and blue, purple, and scarlet thread; with artistic designs
        of cherubim you shall weave them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The length of each curtain shall  be twenty-eight cubits, and the
        width of each curtain four cubits. And every one of the curtains shall have
        the same measurements. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Five curtains shall be coupled to one another, and the  other five
        curtains shall  be coupled to one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And you shall make loops of blue yarn on the edge of the curtain
        on the selvedge of one set, and likewise you shall do on the outer edge of
        the  other curtain of the second set. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Fifty loops you shall make in the one curtain, and fifty loops you
        shall make on the edge of the curtain that is on the end of the second set,
        that the loops may be clasped to one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And you shall make fifty clasps of gold, and couple the curtains together
        with the clasps, so that it may be one tabernacle.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make curtains of goats\u2019 hair, to be a tent
        over the tabernacle. You shall make eleven curtains. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The length of each curtain shall  be thirty cubits, and the width
        of each curtain four cubits; and the eleven curtains shall all have the same
        measurements. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And you shall couple five curtains by themselves and six curtains
        by themselves, and you shall double over the sixth curtain at the forefront
        of the tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall make fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost
        in one set, and fifty loops on the edge of the curtain of the second set. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall make fifty bronze clasps, put the clasps into the loops,
        and couple the tent together, that it may be one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The remnant that remains of the curtains of the tent, the half curtain
        that remains, shall hang over the back of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And a cubit on one side and a cubit on the other side, of what remains
        of the length of the curtains of the tent, shall hang over the sides of the
        tabernacle, on this side and on that side, to cover it.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make a covering of ram skins dyed red for the
        tent, and a covering of badger skins above that."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd for the tabernacle you shall make the boards of acacia
        wood, standing upright. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Ten cubits shall  be the length of a board, and a cubit and a half
        shall  be the width of each board. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Two tenons shall  be in each board for binding one to another. Thus
        you shall make for all the boards of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you shall make the boards for the tabernacle, twenty boards for
        the south side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You shall make forty sockets of silver under the twenty boards: two
        sockets under each of the boards for its two tenons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And for the second side of the tabernacle, the north side, there 
        shall  be twenty boards '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and their forty sockets of silver: two sockets under each of the
        boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the far side of the tabernacle, westward, you shall make six
        boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And you shall also make two boards for the two back corners of the
        tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They shall be coupled together at the bottom and they shall be coupled
        together at the top by one ring. Thus it shall be for both of them. They
        shall be for the two corners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So there shall be eight boards with their sockets of silver\u2014sixteen
        sockets\u2014two sockets under each of the boards."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall make bars of acacia wood: five for the boards
        on one side of the tabernacle, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'five bars for the boards on the other side of the tabernacle, and
        five bars for the boards of the side of the tabernacle, for the far side
        westward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The middle bar shall pass through the midst of the boards from end
        to end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall overlay the boards with gold, make their rings of gold
        as holders for the bars, and overlay the bars with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And you shall raise up the tabernacle according to its pattern which
        you were shown on the mountain.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a veil woven of blue, purple, and scarlet thread,
        and fine woven linen. It shall be woven with an artistic design of cherubim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You shall hang it upon the four pillars of acacia wood overlaid with
        gold. Their hooks shall  be gold, upon four sockets of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And you shall hang the veil from the clasps. Then you shall bring
        the ark of the Testimony in there, behind the veil. The veil shall be a divider
        for you between the holy place and the Most Holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You shall put the mercy seat upon the ark of the Testimony in the
        Most Holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: You shall set the table outside the veil, and the lampstand across
        from the table on the side of the tabernacle toward the south; and you shall
        put the table on the north side.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a screen for the door of the tabernacle, woven 
        of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, made by a weaver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: And you shall make for the screen five pillars of acacia wood, and
        overlay them with gold; their hooks shall  be gold, and you shall cast five
        sockets of bronze for them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Altar of Burnt Offering'
      title: The Altar of Burnt Offering
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CYou shall make an altar of acacia wood, five cubits long and
        five cubits wide\u2014the altar shall be square\u2014and its height shall 
        be three cubits. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall make its horns on its four corners; its horns shall be
        of one piece with it. And you shall overlay it with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Also you shall make its pans to receive its ashes, and its shovels
        and its basins and its forks and its firepans; you shall make all its utensils
        of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall make a grate for it, a network of bronze; and on the network
        you shall make four bronze rings at its four corners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall put it under the rim of the altar beneath, that the network
        may be midway up the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And you shall make poles for the altar, poles of acacia wood, and
        overlay them with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The poles shall be put in the rings, and the poles shall be on the
        two sides of the altar to bear it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Court of the Tabernacle'
      title: The Court of the Tabernacle
      number: 8
      content: You shall make it hollow with boards; as it was shown you on the mountain,
        so shall they make it.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make the court of the tabernacle. For the south
        side there  shall  be hangings for the court made  of fine woven linen, one
        hundred cubits long for one side. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And its twenty pillars and their twenty sockets shall  be bronze.
        The hooks of the pillars and their bands shall  be silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Likewise along the length of the north side there  shall  be hangings
        one hundred cubits long, with its twenty pillars and their twenty sockets
        of bronze, and the hooks of the pillars and their bands of silver.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd along the width of the court on the west side shall  be
        hangings of fifty cubits, with their ten pillars and their ten sockets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The width of the court on the east side shall  be fifty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The hangings on one side of  the  gate  shall  be fifteen cubits,
        with their three pillars and their three sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And on the other side shall  be hangings of fifteen cubits, with their
        three pillars and their three sockets.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CFor the gate of the court there  shall  be a screen twenty
        cubits long, woven  of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen,
        made by a weaver. It shall  have four pillars and four sockets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All the pillars around the court shall have bands of silver; their
        hooks shall  be of silver and their sockets of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The length of the court shall  be one hundred cubits, the width fifty
        throughout, and the height five cubits, made  of fine woven linen, and its
        sockets of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Care of the Lampstand'
      title: The Care of the Lampstand
      number: 19
      content: All the utensils of the tabernacle for all its service, all its pegs,
        and all the pegs of the court, shall  be of bronze.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall command the children of Israel that they bring
        you pure oil of pressed olives for the light, to cause the lamp to burn continually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: In the tabernacle of meeting, outside the veil which is before the
        Testimony, Aaron and his sons shall tend it from evening until morning before
        the Lord. It  shall  be a statute forever to their generations on behalf
        of the children of Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Garments for the Priesthood'
      title: Garments for the Priesthood
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CNow take Aaron your brother, and his sons with him, from among
        the children of Israel, that he may minister to Me as priest, Aaron and Aaron\u2019s
        sons: Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And you shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother, for glory
        and for beauty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So you shall speak to all who  are gifted artisans, whom I have filled
        with the spirit of wisdom, that they may make Aaron\u2019s garments, to consecrate
        him, that he may minister to Me as priest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Ephod'
      title: The Ephod
      number: 4
      content: 'And these are the garments which they shall make: a breastplate,
        an ephod, a robe, a skillfully woven tunic, a turban, and a sash. So they
        shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother and his sons, that he may
        minister to Me as priest.'
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThey shall take the gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread,
        and the fine linen, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and they shall make the ephod of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet
        thread, and fine woven linen, artistically worked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It shall have two shoulder straps joined at its two edges, and so
        it shall be joined together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And the intricately woven band of the ephod, which is on it, shall
        be of the same workmanship, made  of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread,
        and fine woven linen.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThen you shall take two onyx stones and engrave on them the
        names of the sons of Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'six of their names on one stone and six names on the other stone,
        in order of their birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'With the work of an engraver in stone, like the engravings of a signet,
        you shall engrave the two stones with the names of the sons of Israel. You
        shall set them in settings of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you shall put the two stones on the shoulders of the ephod as
        memorial stones for the sons of Israel. So Aaron shall bear their names before
        the Lord on his two shoulders as a memorial. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall also make settings of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Breastplate'
      title: The Breastplate
      number: 14
      content: and you shall make two chains of pure gold like braided cords, and
        fasten the braided chains to the settings.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CYou shall make the breastplate of judgment. Artistically woven
        according to the workmanship of the ephod you shall make it: of gold, blue,
        purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, you shall make it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It shall be doubled into a square: a span shall  be its length, and
        a span shall  be its width. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And you shall put settings of stones in it, four rows of stones:
        The  first row shall  be a sardius, a topaz, and an emerald; this  shall 
        be the first row; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the second row shall  be a turquoise, a sapphire, and a diamond; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They shall be
        set in gold settings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And the stones shall have the names of the sons of Israel, twelve
        according to their names, like the engravings of a signet, each one with
        its own name; they shall be according to the twelve tribes.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYou shall make chains for the breastplate at the end, like
        braided cords of pure gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And you shall make two rings of gold for the breastplate, and put
        the two rings on the two ends of the breastplate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then you shall put the two braided chains of gold in the two rings
        which are on the ends of the breastplate; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: and the other two ends of the two braided chains you shall fasten
        to the two settings, and put them on the shoulder straps of the ephod in
        the front.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CYou shall make two rings of gold, and put them on the two ends
        of the breastplate, on the edge of it, which is on the inner side of the
        ephod. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And two other rings of gold you shall make, and put them on the two
        shoulder straps, underneath the ephod toward its front, right at the seam
        above the intricately woven band of the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: They shall bind the breastplate by means of its rings to the rings
        of the ephod, using a blue cord, so that it is above the intricately woven
        band of the ephod, and so that the breastplate does not come loose from the
        ephod.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CSo Aaron shall bear the names of the sons of Israel on the
        breastplate of judgment over his heart, when he goes into the holy place,
        as a memorial before the Lord continually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Other Priestly Garments'
      title: Other Priestly Garments
      number: 30
      content: "And you shall put in the breastplate of judgment the Urim and the
        Thummim, and they shall be over Aaron\u2019s heart when he goes in before
        the Lord. So Aaron shall bear the judgment of the children of Israel over
        his heart before the Lord continually."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou shall make the robe of the ephod all of blue. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'There shall be an opening for his head in the middle of it; it shall
        have a woven binding all around its opening, like the opening in a coat of
        mail, so that it does not tear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And upon its hem you shall make pomegranates of blue, purple, and
        scarlet, all around its hem, and bells of gold between them all around: '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'a golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate,
        upon the hem of the robe all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: And it shall be upon Aaron when he ministers, and its sound will be
        heard when he goes into the holy place before the Lord and when he comes
        out, that he may not die.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make a plate of pure gold and engrave on it,
        like the engraving of a signet:HOLINESS TO THE LORD."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And you shall put it on a blue cord, that it may be on the turban;
        it shall be on the front of the turban. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "So it shall be on Aaron\u2019s forehead, that Aaron may bear the
        iniquity of the holy things which the children of Israel hallow in all their
        holy gifts; and it shall always be on his forehead, that they may be accepted
        before the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CYou shall skillfully weave the tunic of fine linen thread,
        you shall make the turban of fine linen, and you shall make the sash of woven
        work."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CFor Aaron\u2019s sons you shall make tunics, and you shall
        make sashes for them. And you shall make hats for them, for glory and beauty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'So you shall put them on Aaron your brother and on his sons with
        him. You shall anoint them, consecrate them, and sanctify them, that they
        may minister to Me as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And you shall make for them linen trousers to cover their nakedness;
        they shall reach from the waist to the thighs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: They shall be on Aaron and on his sons when they come into the tabernacle
        of meeting, or when they come near the altar to minister in the holy place,
        that they do not incur iniquity and die. It  shall  be a statute forever
        to him and his descendants after him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Aaron and His Sons Consecrated'
      title: Aaron and His Sons Consecrated
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAnd this is what you shall do to them to hallow them for ministering
        to Me as priests: Take one young bull and two rams without blemish, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and unleavened bread, unleavened cakes mixed with oil, and unleavened
        wafers anointed with oil (you shall make them of wheat flour). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You shall put them in one basket and bring them in the basket, with
        the bull and the two rams.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAnd Aaron and his sons you shall bring to the door of the tabernacle
        of meeting, and you shall wash them with water. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then you shall take the garments, put the tunic on Aaron, and the
        robe of the ephod, the ephod, and the breastplate, and gird him with the
        intricately woven band of the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall put the turban on his head, and put the holy crown on the
        turban. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall take the anointing oil, pour it on his head, and anoint
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then you shall bring his sons and put tunics on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: And you shall gird them with sashes, Aaron and his sons, and put the
        hats on them. The priesthood shall be theirs for a perpetual statute. So
        you shall consecrate Aaron and his sons.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou shall also have the bull brought before the tabernacle
        of meeting, and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands on the head of the
        bull. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then you shall kill the bull before the Lord, by the door of the
        tabernacle of meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall take some of the blood of the bull and put it on the horns
        of the altar with your finger, and pour all the blood beside the base of
        the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And you shall take all the fat that covers the entrails, the fatty
        lobe attached to the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat that is on them,
        and burn them on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But the flesh of the bull, with its skin and its offal, you shall
        burn with fire outside the camp. It is a sin offering.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CYou shall also take one ram, and Aaron and his sons shall put
        their hands on the head of the ram; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and you shall kill the ram, and you shall take its blood and sprinkle
        it all around on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then you shall cut the ram in pieces, wash its entrails and its legs,
        and put them with its pieces and with its head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And you shall burn the whole ram on the altar. It is a burnt offering
        to the Lord; it is a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou shall also take the other ram, and Aaron and his sons shall
        put their hands on the head of the ram. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then you shall kill the ram, and take some of its blood and put it
        on the tip of the right ear of Aaron and on the tip of the right ear of his
        sons, on the thumb of their right hand and on the big toe of their right
        foot, and sprinkle the blood all around on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And you shall take some of the blood that is on the altar, and some
        of the anointing oil, and sprinkle it on Aaron and on his garments, on his
        sons and on the garments of his sons with him; and he and his garments shall
        be hallowed, and his sons and his sons\u2019 garments with him."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAlso you shall take the fat of the ram, the fat tail, the fat
        that covers the entrails, the fatty lobe attached  to the liver, the two
        kidneys and the fat on them, the right thigh (for it is a ram of consecration), "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'one loaf of bread, one cake made  with oil, and one wafer from the
        basket of the unleavened bread that is before the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and you shall put all these in the hands of Aaron and in the hands
        of his sons, and you shall wave them as a wave offering before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: You shall receive them back from their hands and burn them on the
        altar as a burnt offering, as a sweet aroma before the Lord. It is an offering
        made by fire to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThen you shall take the breast of the ram of Aaron\u2019s consecration
        and wave it as a wave offering before the Lord; and it shall be your portion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And from the ram of the consecration you shall consecrate the breast
        of the wave offering which is waved, and the thigh of the heave offering
        which is raised, of that which is for Aaron and of that which is for his
        sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: It shall be from the children of Israel for Aaron and his sons by
        a statute forever. For it is a heave offering; it shall be a heave offering
        from the children of Israel from the sacrifices of their peace offerings,
        that  is, their heave offering to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAnd the holy garments of Aaron shall be his sons\u2019 after
        him, to be anointed in them and to be consecrated in them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: That son who becomes priest in his place shall put them on for seven
        days, when he enters the tabernacle of meeting to minister in the holy place.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall take the ram of the consecration and boil its
        flesh in the holy place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then Aaron and his sons shall eat the flesh of the ram, and the bread
        that is in the basket, by the door of the tabernacle of meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They shall eat those things with which the atonement was made, to
        consecrate and to sanctify them; but an outsider shall not eat them, because
        they are holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And if any of the flesh of the consecration offerings, or of the bread,
        remains until the morning, then you shall burn the remainder with fire. It
        shall not be eaten, because it is holy.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThus you shall do to Aaron and his sons, according to all that
        I have commanded you. Seven days you shall consecrate them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And you shall offer a bull every day as a sin offering for atonement.
        You shall cleanse the altar when you make atonement for it, and you shall
        anoint it to sanctify it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: The Daily Offerings'
      title: The Daily Offerings
      number: 37
      content: Seven days you shall make atonement for the altar and sanctify it.
        And the altar shall be most holy. Whatever touches the altar must be holy.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CNow this is what you shall offer on the altar: two lambs of
        the first year, day by day continually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'One lamb you shall offer in the morning, and the other lamb you shall
        offer at twilight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'With the one lamb shall be one-tenth of  an  ephah of flour mixed
        with one-fourth of a hin of pressed oil, and one-fourth of a hin of wine
        as a drink offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And the other lamb you shall offer at twilight; and you shall offer
        with it the grain offering and the drink offering, as in the morning, for
        a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'This  shall  be  a continual burnt offering throughout your generations
        at the door of the tabernacle of meeting before the Lord, where I will meet
        you to speak with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And there I will meet with the children of Israel, and the  tabernacle 
        shall be sanctified by My glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'So I will consecrate the tabernacle of meeting and the altar. I will
        also consecrate both Aaron and his sons to minister to Me as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'I will dwell among the children of Israel and will be their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: And they shall know that I am the Lord their God, who brought them
        up out of the land of Egypt, that I may dwell among them. I am the Lord their
        God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Altar of Incense'
      title: The Altar of Incense
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CYou shall make an altar to burn incense on; you shall make
        it of acacia wood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "A cubit shall  be its length and a cubit its width\u2014it shall
        be square\u2014and two cubits shall  be its height. Its horns shall  be of
        one piece with it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you shall overlay its top, its sides all around, and its horns
        with pure gold; and you shall make for it a molding of gold all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Two gold rings you shall make for it, under the molding on both its
        sides. You shall place them on its two sides, and they will be holders for
        the poles with which to bear it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall make the poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And you shall put it before the veil that is before the ark of the
        Testimony, before the mercy seat that is over the Testimony, where I will
        meet with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAaron shall burn on it sweet incense every morning; when he
        tends the lamps, he shall burn incense on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when Aaron lights the lamps at twilight, he shall burn incense
        on it, a perpetual incense before the Lord throughout your generations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall not offer strange incense on it, or a burnt offering, or
        a grain offering; nor shall you pour a drink offering on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Ransom Money'
      title: The Ransom Money
      number: 10
      content: "And Aaron shall make atonement upon its horns once a year with the
        blood of the sin offering of atonement; once a year he shall make atonement
        upon it throughout your generations. It is most holy to the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you take the census of the children of Israel for their
        number, then every man shall give a ransom for himself to the Lord, when
        you number them, that there may be no plague among them when you number them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This is what everyone among those who are numbered shall give: half
        a shekel according to the shekel of the sanctuary (a shekel is twenty gerahs).
        The half-shekel shall  be an offering to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Everyone included among those who are numbered, from twenty years
        old and above, shall give an offering to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The rich shall not give more and the poor shall not give less than
        half a shekel, when you give an offering to the Lord, to make atonement for
        yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Bronze Laver'
      title: The Bronze Laver
      number: 16
      content: "And you shall take the atonement money of the children of Israel,
        and shall appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of meeting, that it
        may be a memorial for the children of Israel before the Lord, to make atonement
        for yourselves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make a laver of bronze, with its base also of
        bronze, for washing. You shall put it between the tabernacle of meeting and
        the altar. And you shall put water in it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'for Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet in water
        from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When they go into the tabernacle of meeting, or when they come near
        the altar to minister, to burn an offering made by fire to the Lord, they
        shall wash with water, lest they die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Holy Anointing Oil'
      title: The Holy Anointing Oil
      number: 21
      content: "So they shall wash their hands and their feet, lest they die. And
        it shall be a statute forever to them\u2014to him and his descendants throughout
        their generations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Moreover the Lord spoke to Moses, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAlso take for yourself quality spices\u2014five hundred shekels
        of liquid myrrh, half as much sweet-smelling cinnamon (two hundred and fifty
        shekels), two hundred and fifty shekels of sweet-smelling cane, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'five hundred shekels of cassia, according to the shekel of the sanctuary,
        and a hin of olive oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And you shall make from these a holy anointing oil, an ointment compounded
        according to the art of the perfumer. It shall be a holy anointing oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'With it you shall anoint the tabernacle of meeting and the ark of
        the Testimony; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the table and all its utensils, the lampstand and its utensils, and
        the altar of incense; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and the laver
        and its base. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall consecrate them, that they may be most holy; whatever touches
        them must be holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And you shall anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that
        they may minister to Me as priests.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall speak to the children of Israel, saying: \u2018This
        shall be a holy anointing oil to Me throughout your generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "It shall not be poured on man\u2019s flesh; nor shall you make any 
        other like it, according to its composition. It is holy, and it shall be
        holy to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: The Incense'
      title: The Incense
      number: 33
      content: "Whoever compounds any like it, or whoever puts any of it on an outsider,
        shall be cut off from his people.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses: \u201CTake sweet spices, stacte and onycha
        and galbanum, and pure frankincense with these sweet spices; there shall
        be equal amounts of each. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'You shall make of these an incense, a compound according to the art
        of the perfumer, salted, pure, and holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And you shall beat some of it very fine, and put some of it before
        the Testimony in the tabernacle of meeting where I will meet with you. It
        shall be most holy to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But as  for the incense which you shall make, you shall not make
        any for yourselves, according to its composition. It shall be to you holy
        for the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Whoever makes any like it, to smell it, he shall be cut off from
        his people.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Artisans for Building the Tabernacle'
      title: Artisans for Building the Tabernacle
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSee, I have called by name Bezalel the son of Uri, the son
        of Hur, of the tribe of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And I have filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom, in understanding,
        in knowledge, and in all manner  of workmanship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'to design artistic works, to work in gold, in silver, in bronze, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: in cutting jewels for setting, in carving wood, and to work in all
        manner  of workmanship.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd I, indeed I, have appointed with him Aholiab the son of
        Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan; and I have put wisdom in the hearts of all
        the gifted artisans, that they may make all that I have commanded you: "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "the tabernacle of meeting, the ark of the Testimony and the mercy
        seat that is on it, and all the furniture of the tabernacle\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the table and its utensils, the pure gold lampstand with all its
        utensils, the altar of incense, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and the laver
        and its base\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the garments of ministry, the holy garments for Aaron the priest
        and the garments of his sons, to minister as priests, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Sabbath Law'
      title: The Sabbath Law
      number: 11
      content: "and the anointing oil and sweet incense for the holy place. According
        to all that I have commanded you they shall do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CSpeak also to the children of Israel, saying: \u2018Surely
        My Sabbaths you shall keep, for it is a sign between Me and you throughout
        your generations, that you may know that I am the Lord who sanctifies you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall keep the Sabbath, therefore, for it  is holy to you. Everyone
        who profanes it shall surely be put to death; for whoever does any work on
        it, that person shall be cut off from among his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Work shall be done for six days, but the seventh is the Sabbath of
        rest, holy to the Lord. Whoever does any work on the Sabbath day, he shall
        surely be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore the children of Israel shall keep the Sabbath, to observe
        the Sabbath throughout their generations as a perpetual covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "It is  a sign between Me and the children of Israel forever; for
        in six days the Lord made the heavens and the earth, and on the seventh day
        He rested and was refreshed.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And when He had made an end of speaking with him on Mount Sinai, He
        gave Moses two tablets of the Testimony, tablets of stone, written with the
        finger of God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Gold Calf'
      title: The Gold Calf
      number: 1
      content: "Now when the people saw that Moses delayed coming down from the mountain,
        the people gathered together to Aaron, and said to him, \u201CCome, make
        us gods that shall go before us; for as  for this Moses, the man who brought
        us up out of the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Aaron said to them, \u201CBreak off the golden earrings which
        are in the ears of your wives, your sons, and your daughters, and bring them
        to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So all the people broke off the golden earrings which were in their
        ears, and brought them to Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he received the  gold from their hand, and he fashioned it with
        an engraving tool, and made a molded calf.Then they said, \u201CThis is your
        god, O Israel, that brought you out of the land of Egypt!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So when Aaron saw it, he built an altar before it. And Aaron made
        a proclamation and said, \u201CTomorrow is a feast to the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Then they rose early on the next day, offered burnt offerings, and
        brought peace offerings; and the people sat down to eat and drink, and rose
        up to play.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo, get down! For your people whom
        you brought out of the land of Egypt have corrupted themselves.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They have turned aside quickly out of the way which I commanded them.
        They have made themselves a molded calf, and worshiped it and sacrificed
        to it, and said, \u2018This is your god, O Israel, that brought you out of
        the land of Egypt!\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CI have seen this people, and indeed
        it is a stiff-necked people! "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now therefore, let Me alone, that My wrath may burn hot against them
        and I may consume them. And I will make of you a great nation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Moses pleaded with the Lord his God, and said: \u201CLord, why
        does Your wrath burn hot against Your people whom You have brought out of
        the land of Egypt with great power and with a mighty hand? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Why should the Egyptians speak, and say, \u2018He brought them out
        to harm them, to kill them in the mountains, and to consume them from the
        face of the earth\u2019? Turn from Your fierce wrath, and relent from this
        harm to Your people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, Your servants, to whom You swore
        by Your own self, and said to them, \u2018I will multiply your descendants
        as the stars of heaven; and all this land that I have spoken of I give to
        your descendants, and they shall inherit it forever.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So the Lord  relented from the harm which He said He would do to His
        people.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Moses turned and went down from the mountain, and the two tablets
        of the Testimony were in his hand. The tablets were written on both sides;
        on the one side and on the other they were written. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Now the tablets were the work of God, and the writing was the writing
        of God engraved on the tablets.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And when Joshua heard the noise of the people as they shouted, he
        said to Moses, \u201CThere  is a noise of war in the camp.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But he said:\u201CIt  is not the noise of the shout of victory,Nor
        the noise of the cry of defeat,But the sound of singing I hear.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So it was, as soon as he came near the camp, that he saw the calf
        and the dancing. So Moses\u2019 anger became hot, and he cast the tablets
        out of his hands and broke them at the foot of the mountain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then he took the calf which they had made, burned it in the fire,
        and ground it to powder; and he scattered it on the water and made the children
        of Israel drink it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Moses said to Aaron, \u201CWhat did this people do to you that
        you have brought so great a sin upon them?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Aaron said, \u201CDo not let the anger of my lord become hot.
        You know the people, that they are  set on evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For they said to me, \u2018Make us gods that shall go before us;
        as  for this Moses, the man who brought us out of the land of Egypt, we do
        not know what has become of him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And I said to them, \u2018Whoever has any gold, let them break it
        off.\u2019 So they gave it to me, and I cast it into the fire, and this calf
        came out.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now when Moses saw that the people were  unrestrained (for Aaron
        had not restrained them, to their shame among their enemies), '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then Moses stood in the entrance of the camp, and said, \u201CWhoever
        is on the Lord\u2019s side\u2014come to me!\u201D And all the sons of Levi
        gathered themselves together to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel: \u2018Let
        every man put his sword on his side, and go in and out from entrance to entrance
        throughout the camp, and let every man kill his brother, every man his companion,
        and every man his neighbor.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So the sons of Levi did according to the word of Moses. And about
        three thousand men of the people fell that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CConsecrate yourselves today to the Lord, that
        He may bestow on you a blessing this day, for every man has opposed his son
        and his brother.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now it came to pass on the next day that Moses said to the people,
        \u201CYou have committed a great sin. So now I will go up to the Lord; perhaps
        I can make atonement for your sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Moses returned to the Lord and said, \u201COh, these people
        have committed a great sin, and have made for themselves a god of gold! "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Yet now, if You will forgive their sin\u2014but if not, I pray, blot
        me out of Your book which You have written.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWhoever has sinned against Me,
        I will blot him out of My book. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Now therefore, go, lead the people to the  place of which I have
        spoken to you. Behold, My Angel shall go before you. Nevertheless, in the
        day when I visit for punishment, I will visit punishment upon them for their
        sin.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: So the Lord plagued the people because of what they did with the calf
        which Aaron made.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Command to Leave Sinai'
      title: The Command to Leave Sinai
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CDepart and go up from here, you
        and the people whom you have brought out of the land of Egypt, to the land
        of which I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, \u2018To your descendants
        I will give it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I will send My Angel before you, and I will drive out the Canaanite
        and the Amorite and the Hittite and the Perizzite and the Hivite and the
        Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Go  up  to a land flowing with milk and honey; for I will not go
        up in your midst, lest I consume you on the way, for you are  a stiff-necked
        people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when the people heard this bad news, they mourned, and no one
        put on his ornaments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For the Lord had said to Moses, \u201CSay to the children of Israel,
        \u2018You are a stiff-necked people. I could come up into your midst in one
        moment and consume you. Now therefore, take off your ornaments, that I may
        know what to do to you.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Moses Meets with the Lord'
      title: Moses Meets with the Lord
      number: 6
      content: So the children of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments by
        Mount Horeb.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Moses took his tent and pitched it outside the camp, far from the
        camp, and called it the tabernacle of meeting. And it came to pass that everyone
        who sought the Lord went out to the tabernacle of meeting which was outside
        the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So it was, whenever Moses went out to the tabernacle, that all the
        people rose, and each man stood at his tent door and watched Moses until
        he had gone into the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Moses entered the tabernacle, that the
        pillar of cloud descended and stood at the door of the tabernacle, and the 
        Lord  talked with Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All the people saw the pillar of cloud standing at the tabernacle
        door, and all the people rose and worshiped, each man in his tent door. '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: The Promise of God\u2019s Presence"
      title: "The Promise of God\u2019s Presence"
      number: 11
      content: So the Lord spoke to Moses face to face, as a man speaks to his friend.
        And he would return to the camp, but his servant Joshua the son of Nun, a
        young man, did not depart from the tabernacle.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Moses said to the Lord, \u201CSee, You say to me, \u2018Bring
        up this people.\u2019 But You have not let me know whom You will send with
        me. Yet You have said, \u2018I know you by name, and you have also found
        grace in My sight.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now therefore, I pray, if I have found grace in Your sight, show
        me now Your way, that I may know You and that I may find grace in Your sight.
        And consider that this nation is  Your people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And He said, \u201CMy Presence will go with  you, and I will give
        you rest.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he said to Him, \u201CIf Your Presence does not go with  us,
        do not bring us up from here. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For how then will it be known that Your people and I have found grace
        in Your sight, except You go with us? So we shall be separate, Your people
        and I, from all the people who are upon the face of the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the Lord said to Moses, \u201CI will also do this thing that you
        have spoken; for you have found grace in My sight, and I know you by name.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CPlease, show me Your glory.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then He said, \u201CI will make all My goodness pass before you,
        and I will proclaim the name of the Lord before you. I will be gracious to
        whom I will be gracious, and I will have compassion on whom I will have compassion.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But He said, \u201CYou cannot see My face; for no man shall see Me,
        and live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CHere is a place by Me, and you shall stand
        on the rock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So it shall be, while My glory passes by, that I will put you in
        the cleft of the rock, and will cover you with My hand while I pass by. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then I will take away My hand, and you shall see My back; but My
        face shall not be seen.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moses Makes New Tablets'
      title: Moses Makes New Tablets
      number: 1
      content: "And the Lord said to Moses, \u201CCut two tablets of stone like the
        first ones, and I will write on these tablets the words that were on the
        first tablets which you broke. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So be ready in the morning, and come up in the morning to Mount Sinai,
        and present yourself to Me there on the top of the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And no man shall come up with you, and let no man be seen throughout
        all the mountain; let neither flocks nor herds feed before that mountain.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So he cut two tablets of stone like the first ones. Then Moses rose
        early in the morning and went up Mount Sinai, as the Lord had commanded him;
        and he took in his hand the two tablets of stone.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the Lord descended in the cloud and stood with him there, and
        proclaimed the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the Lord passed before him and proclaimed, \u201CThe Lord, the
        Lord  God, merciful and gracious, longsuffering, and abounding in goodness
        and truth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "keeping mercy for thousands, forgiving iniquity and transgression
        and sin, by no means clearing the  guilty, visiting the iniquity of the fathers
        upon the children and the children\u2019s children to the third and the fourth
        generation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Moses made haste and bowed his head toward the earth, and worshiped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Covenant Renewed'
      title: The Covenant Renewed
      number: 9
      content: "Then he said, \u201CIf now I have found grace in Your sight, O Lord,
        let my Lord, I pray, go among us, even though we are a stiff-necked people;
        and pardon our iniquity and our sin, and take us as Your inheritance.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And He said: \u201CBehold, I make a covenant. Before all your people
        I will do marvels such as have not been done in all the earth, nor in any
        nation; and all the people among whom you are shall see the work of the Lord.
        For it is  an awesome thing that I will do with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Observe what I command you this day. Behold, I am driving out from
        before you the Amorite and the Canaanite and the Hittite and the Perizzite
        and the Hivite and the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Take heed to yourself, lest you make a covenant with the inhabitants
        of the land where you are going, lest it be a snare in your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But you shall destroy their altars, break their sacred pillars, and
        cut down their wooden images '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '(for you shall worship no other god, for the Lord, whose name is
        Jealous, is a jealous God), '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'lest you make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land, and they
        play the harlot with their gods and make sacrifice to their gods, and one 
        of  them  invites you and you eat of his sacrifice, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: and you take of his daughters for your sons, and his daughters play
        the harlot with their gods and make your sons play the harlot with their
        gods.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou shall make no molded gods for yourselves."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThe Feast of Unleavened Bread you shall keep. Seven days you
        shall eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, in the appointed time of
        the month of Abib; for in the month of Abib you came out from Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAll that open the womb are Mine, and every male firstborn among
        your livestock, whether ox or sheep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the firstborn of a donkey you shall redeem with a lamb. And if
        you will not redeem him, then you shall break his neck. All the firstborn
        of your sons you shall redeem.\u201CAnd none shall appear before Me empty-handed."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CSix days you shall work, but on the seventh day you shall rest;
        in plowing time and in harvest you shall rest."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall observe the Feast of Weeks, of the firstfruits
        of wheat harvest, and the Feast of Ingathering at the year\u2019s end."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThree times in the year all your men shall appear before the
        Lord, the Lord God of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: For I will cast out the nations before you and enlarge your borders;
        neither will any man covet your land when you go up to appear before the
        Lord your God three times in the year.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CYou shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leaven,
        nor shall the sacrifice of the Feast of the Passover be left until morning."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThe first of the firstfruits of your land you shall bring to
        the house of the Lord your God. You shall not boil a young goat in its mother\u2019s
        milk.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWrite these words, for according
        to the tenor of these words I have made a covenant with you and with Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Shining Face of Moses'
      title: The Shining Face of Moses
      number: 28
      content: So he was there with the Lord forty days and forty nights; he neither
        ate bread nor drank water. And He wrote on the tablets the words of the covenant,
        the Ten Commandments.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Now it was so, when Moses came down from Mount Sinai (and the two
        tablets of the Testimony were in Moses\u2019 hand when he came down from
        the mountain), that Moses did not know that the skin of his face shone while
        he talked with Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So when Aaron and all the children of Israel saw Moses, behold, the
        skin of his face shone, and they were afraid to come near him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then Moses called to them, and Aaron and all the rulers of the congregation
        returned to him; and Moses talked with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Afterward all the children of Israel came near, and he gave them
        as commandments all that the Lord had spoken with him on Mount Sinai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And when Moses had finished speaking with them, he put a veil on
        his face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But whenever Moses went in before the Lord to speak with Him, he
        would take the veil off until he came out; and he would come out and speak
        to the children of Israel whatever he had been commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And whenever the children of Israel saw the face of Moses, that the
        skin of Moses\u2019 face shone, then Moses would put the veil on his face
        again, until he went in to speak with Him."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sabbath Regulations'
      title: Sabbath Regulations
      number: 1
      content: "Then Moses gathered all the congregation of the children of Israel
        together, and said to them, \u201CThese are the words which the Lord has
        commanded you to do: "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Work shall be done for six days, but the seventh day shall be a holy
        day for you, a Sabbath of rest to the Lord. Whoever does any work on it shall
        be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Offerings for the Tabernacle'
      title: Offerings for the Tabernacle
      number: 3
      content: "You shall kindle no fire throughout your dwellings on the Sabbath
        day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Moses spoke to all the congregation of the children of Israel,
        saying, \u201CThis is the thing which the Lord commanded, saying: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Take from among you an offering to the Lord. Whoever is of
        a willing heart, let him bring it as an offering to the Lord: gold, silver,
        and bronze; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "blue, purple, and scarlet thread, fine linen, and goats\u2019 hair;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'ram skins dyed red, badger skins, and acacia wood; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'oil for the light, and spices for the anointing oil and for the sweet
        incense; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Articles of the Tabernacle'
      title: Articles of the Tabernacle
      number: 9
      content: onyx stones, and stones to be set in the ephod and in the breastplate.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018All who  are gifted artisans among you shall come and make
        all that the Lord has commanded: "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the tabernacle, its tent, its covering, its clasps, its boards, its
        bars, its pillars, and its sockets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the ark and its poles, with the mercy seat, and the veil of the covering; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the table and its poles, all its utensils, and the showbread; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'also the lampstand for the light, its utensils, its lamps, and the
        oil for the light; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the incense altar, its poles, the anointing oil, the sweet incense,
        and the screen for the door at the entrance of the tabernacle; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the altar of burnt offering with its bronze grating, its poles, all
        its utensils, and the laver and its base; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the hangings of the court, its pillars, their sockets, and the screen
        for the gate of the court; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the pegs of the tabernacle, the pegs of the court, and their cords; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Tabernacle Offerings Presented'
      title: The Tabernacle Offerings Presented
      number: 19
      content: "the garments of ministry, for ministering in the holy place\u2014the
        holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons, to minister
        as priests.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And all the congregation of the children of Israel departed from
        the presence of Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then everyone came whose heart was stirred, and everyone whose spirit
        was willing, and they brought the Lord\u2019s offering for the work of the
        tabernacle of meeting, for all its service, and for the holy garments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They came, both men and women, as many as had a willing heart, and
        brought earrings and nose rings, rings and necklaces, all jewelry of gold,
        that is, every man who made an offering of gold to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And every man, with whom was found blue, purple, and scarlet thread,
        fine linen, and goats\u2019 hair, red skins of rams, and badger skins, brought
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Everyone who offered an offering of silver or bronze brought the
        Lord\u2019s offering. And everyone with whom was found acacia wood for any
        work of the service, brought it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'All the women who  were  gifted artisans spun yarn with their hands,
        and brought what they had spun, of blue, purple, and scarlet, and fine linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And all the women whose hearts stirred with wisdom spun yarn of goats\u2019
        hair.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The rulers brought onyx stones, and the stones to be set in the ephod
        and in the breastplate, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and spices and oil for the light, for the anointing oil, and for
        the sweet incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Artisans Called by God'
      title: The Artisans Called by God
      number: 29
      content: The children of Israel brought a freewill offering to the Lord, all
        the men and women whose hearts were willing to bring material for all kinds
        of work which the Lord, by the hand of Moses, had commanded to be done.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Moses said to the children of Israel, \u201CSee, the Lord has
        called by name Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and He has filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom and understanding,
        in knowledge and all manner of workmanship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'to design artistic works, to work in gold and silver and bronze, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: in cutting jewels for setting, in carving wood, and to work in all
        manner of artistic workmanship.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CAnd He has put in his heart the ability to teach, in him and
        Aholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "He has filled them with skill to do all manner of work of the engraver
        and the designer and the tapestry maker, in blue, purple, and scarlet thread,
        and fine linen, and of the weaver\u2014those who do every work and those
        who design artistic works."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The People Give More than Enough'
      title: The People Give More than Enough
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAnd Bezalel and Aholiab, and every gifted artisan in whom the
        Lord has put wisdom and understanding, to know how to do all manner of work
        for the service of the sanctuary, shall do according to all that the Lord
        has commanded.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Moses called Bezalel and Aholiab, and every gifted artisan in
        whose heart the Lord had put wisdom, everyone whose heart was stirred, to
        come and do the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they received from Moses all the offering which the children
        of Israel had brought for the work of the service of making the sanctuary.
        So they continued bringing to him freewill offerings every morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then all the craftsmen who were doing all the work of the sanctuary
        came, each from the work he was doing, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and they spoke to Moses, saying, \u201CThe people bring much more
        than enough for the service of the work which the Lord commanded us to do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Moses gave a commandment, and they caused it to be proclaimed
        throughout the camp, saying, \u201CLet neither man nor woman do any more
        work for the offering of the sanctuary.\u201D And the people were restrained
        from bringing, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Building the Tabernacle'
      title: Building the Tabernacle
      number: 7
      content: "for the material they had was sufficient for all the work to be done\u2014indeed
        too much."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then all the gifted artisans among them who worked on the tabernacle
        made ten curtains woven of fine linen, and of blue, purple, and scarlet thread;
        with artistic designs of cherubim they made them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The length of each curtain was twenty-eight cubits, and the width
        of each curtain four cubits; the curtains were all the same size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he coupled five curtains to one another, and the  other five
        curtains he coupled to one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He made loops of blue yarn on the edge of the curtain on the selvedge
        of one set; likewise he did on the outer edge of the  other curtain of the
        second set. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Fifty loops he made on one curtain, and fifty loops he made on the
        edge of the curtain on the end of the second set; the loops held one curtain
        to another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And he made fifty clasps of gold, and coupled the curtains to one
        another with the clasps, that it might be one tabernacle.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He made curtains of goats\u2019 hair for the tent over the tabernacle;
        he made eleven curtains. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The length of each curtain was thirty cubits, and the width of each
        curtain four cubits; the eleven curtains were the same size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He coupled five curtains by themselves and six curtains by themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost
        in one set, and fifty loops he made on the edge of the curtain of the second
        set. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He also made fifty bronze clasps to couple the tent together, that
        it might be one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then he made a covering for the tent of ram skins dyed red, and a
        covering of badger skins above that.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the tabernacle he made boards of acacia wood, standing upright. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The length of each board was ten cubits, and the width of each board
        a cubit and a half. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Each board had two tenons for binding one to another. Thus he made
        for all the boards of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he made boards for the tabernacle, twenty boards for the south
        side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Forty sockets of silver he made to go under the twenty boards: two
        sockets under each of the boards for its two tenons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And for the other side of the tabernacle, the north side, he made
        twenty boards '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and their forty sockets of silver: two sockets under each of the
        boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For the west side of the tabernacle he made six boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He also made two boards for the two back corners of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And they were coupled at the bottom and coupled together at the top
        by one ring. Thus he made both of them for the two corners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So there were eight boards and their sockets\u2014sixteen sockets
        of silver\u2014two sockets under each of the boards."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And he made bars of acacia wood: five for the boards on one side
        of the tabernacle, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'five bars for the boards on the other side of the tabernacle, and
        five bars for the boards of the tabernacle on the far side westward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he made the middle bar to pass through the boards from one end
        to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: He overlaid the boards with gold, made their rings of gold to  be
        holders for the bars, and overlaid the bars with gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And he made a veil of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine
        woven linen; it was worked with an artistic design of cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: He made for it four pillars of acacia wood, and overlaid them with
        gold, with their hooks of gold; and he cast four sockets of silver for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He also made a screen for the tabernacle door, of blue, purple, and
        scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, made by a weaver, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: and its five pillars with their hooks. And he overlaid their capitals
        and their rings with gold, but their five sockets were bronze.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Making the Ark of the Testimony'
      title: Making the Ark of the Testimony
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Bezalel made the ark of acacia wood; two and a half cubits was
        its length, a cubit and a half its width, and a cubit and a half its height. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He overlaid it with pure gold inside and outside, and made a molding
        of gold all around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he cast for it four rings of gold to  be  set in its four corners:
        two rings on one side, and two rings on the other side of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He made poles of acacia wood, and overlaid them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he put the poles into the rings at the sides of the ark, to bear
        the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He also made the mercy seat of pure gold; two and a half cubits was
        its length and a cubit and a half its width. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He made two cherubim of beaten gold; he made them of one piece at
        the two ends of the mercy seat: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'one cherub at one end on this side, and the other cherub at the other
        end on that side. He made the cherubim at the two ends of  one  piece with
        the mercy seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Making the Table for the Showbread'
      title: Making the Table for the Showbread
      number: 9
      content: The cherubim spread out their wings above, and covered the mercy seat
        with their wings. They faced one another; the faces of the cherubim were
        toward the mercy seat.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He made the table of acacia wood; two cubits was its length, a cubit
        its width, and a cubit and a half its height. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he overlaid it with pure gold, and made a molding of gold all
        around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Also he made a frame of a handbreadth all around it, and made a molding
        of gold for the frame all around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he cast for it four rings of gold, and put the rings on the four
        corners that were at its four legs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The rings were close to the frame, as holders for the poles to bear
        the table. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he made the poles of acacia wood to bear the table, and overlaid
        them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Making the Gold Lampstand'
      title: Making the Gold Lampstand
      number: 16
      content: 'He made of pure gold the utensils which were on the table: its dishes,
        its cups, its bowls, and its pitchers for pouring.'
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He also made the lampstand of pure gold; of hammered work he made
        the lampstand. Its shaft, its branches, its bowls, its ornamental knobs,
        and its flowers were of the same piece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And six branches came out of its sides: three branches of the lampstand
        out of one side, and three branches of the lampstand out of the other side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "There were three bowls made like almond blossoms on one branch, with
        an ornamental knob and a flower, and three bowls made like almond blossoms
        on the other branch, with an ornamental knob and a flower\u2014and so for
        the six branches coming out of the lampstand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And on the lampstand itself were four bowls made like almond blossoms,
        each with its ornamental knob and flower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'There  was a knob under the first two branches of the same, a knob
        under the second two branches of the same, and a knob under the third two
        branches of the same, according to the six branches extending from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Their knobs and their branches were of one piece; all of it was one
        hammered piece of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he made its seven lamps, its wick-trimmers, and its trays of
        pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Making the Altar of Incense'
      title: Making the Altar of Incense
      number: 24
      content: Of a talent of pure gold he made it, with all its utensils.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He made the incense altar of acacia wood. Its length was a cubit
        and its width a cubit\u2014it  was square\u2014and two cubits was its height.
        Its horns were of  one  piece with it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And he overlaid it with pure gold: its top, its sides all around,
        and its horns. He also made for it a molding of gold all around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He made two rings of gold for it under its molding, by its two corners
        on both sides, as holders for the poles with which to bear it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Making the Anointing Oil and the Incense'
      title: Making the Anointing Oil and the Incense
      number: 28
      content: And he made the poles of acacia wood, and overlaid them with gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: He also made the holy anointing oil and the pure incense of sweet
        spices, according to the work of the perfumer.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Making the Altar of Burnt Offering'
      title: Making the Altar of Burnt Offering
      number: 1
      content: "He made the altar of burnt offering of acacia wood; five cubits was
        its length and five cubits its width\u2014it  was square\u2014and its height
        was three cubits. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He made its horns on its four corners; the horns were of  one  piece
        with it. And he overlaid it with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He made all the utensils for the altar: the pans, the shovels, the
        basins, the forks, and the firepans; all its utensils he made of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he made a grate of bronze network for the altar, under its rim,
        midway from the bottom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He cast four rings for the four corners of the bronze grating, as
        holders for the poles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he made the poles of acacia wood, and overlaid them with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Making the Bronze Laver'
      title: Making the Bronze Laver
      number: 7
      content: Then he put the poles into the rings on the sides of the altar, with
        which to bear it. He made the altar hollow with boards.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Making the Court of the Tabernacle'
      title: Making the Court of the Tabernacle
      number: 8
      content: He made the laver of bronze and its base of bronze, from the bronze
        mirrors of the serving women who assembled at the door of the tabernacle
        of meeting.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then he made the court on the south side; the hangings of the court
        were  of fine woven linen, one hundred cubits long. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'There were twenty pillars for them, with twenty bronze sockets. The
        hooks of the pillars and their bands were silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On the north side the  hangings  were one hundred cubits long, with
        twenty pillars and their twenty bronze sockets. The hooks of the pillars
        and their bands were silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And on the west side there  were hangings of fifty cubits, with ten
        pillars and their ten sockets. The hooks of the pillars and their bands were
        silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the east side the  hangings  were fifty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The hangings of one side of  the  gate  were fifteen cubits long,
        with their three pillars and their three sockets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the same for the other side of the court gate; on this side and
        that were hangings of fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and their
        three sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'All the hangings of the court all around were  of fine woven linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sockets for the pillars were bronze, the hooks of the pillars
        and their bands were silver, and the overlay of their capitals was silver;
        and all the pillars of the court had bands of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The screen for the gate of the court was woven of blue, purple, and
        scarlet thread, and of fine woven linen. The length was twenty cubits, and
        the height along its width was five cubits, corresponding to the hangings
        of the court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And there  were four pillars with their four sockets of bronze; their
        hooks were silver, and the overlay of their capitals and their bands was
        silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Materials of the Tabernacle'
      title: Materials of the Tabernacle
      number: 20
      content: All the pegs of the tabernacle, and of the court all around, were
        bronze.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: This is the inventory of the tabernacle, the tabernacle of the Testimony,
        which was counted according to the commandment of Moses, for the service
        of the Levites, by the hand of Ithamar, son of Aaron the priest.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah, made
        all that the Lord had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And with him was  Aholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan,
        an engraver and designer, a weaver of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and
        of fine linen.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All the gold that was used in all the work of the holy place, that
        is, the gold of the offering, was twenty-nine talents and seven hundred and
        thirty shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the silver from those who were numbered of the congregation was
        one hundred talents and one thousand seven hundred and seventy-five shekels,
        according to the shekel of the sanctuary: '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'a bekah for each man (that  is, half a shekel, according to the shekel
        of the sanctuary), for everyone included in the numbering from twenty years
        old and above, for six hundred and three thousand, five hundred and fifty
        men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And from the hundred talents of silver were cast the sockets of the
        sanctuary and the bases of the veil: one hundred sockets from the hundred
        talents, one talent for each socket. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Then from the one thousand seven hundred and seventy-five shekels
        he made hooks for the pillars, overlaid their capitals, and made bands for
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The offering of bronze was seventy talents and two thousand four
        hundred shekels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And with it he made the sockets for the door of the tabernacle of
        meeting, the bronze altar, the bronze grating for it, and all the utensils
        for the altar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: the sockets for the court all around, the bases for the court gate,
        all the pegs for the tabernacle, and all the pegs for the court all around.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Making the Garments of the PriesthoodMaking the Ephod'
      title: Making the Garments of the PriesthoodMaking the Ephod
      number: 1
      content: Of the blue, purple, and scarlet thread they made garments of ministry,
        for ministering in the holy place, and made the holy garments for Aaron,
        as the Lord had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He made the ephod of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and
        of fine woven linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they beat the gold into thin sheets and cut it  into threads,
        to work it in with the blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and the fine linen,
        into artistic designs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They made shoulder straps for it to couple it together; it was coupled
        together at its two edges. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And the intricately woven band of his ephod that was on it was of
        the same workmanship, woven  of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and
        of fine woven linen, as the Lord had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And they set onyx stones, enclosed in settings of gold; they were
        engraved, as signets are engraved, with the names of the sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Making the Breastplate'
      title: Making the Breastplate
      number: 7
      content: He put them on the shoulders of the ephod as  memorial stones for
        the sons of Israel, as the Lord had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he made the breastplate, artistically woven like the workmanship
        of the ephod, of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and of fine woven
        linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They made the breastplate square by doubling it; a span was its length
        and a span its width when doubled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they set in it four rows of stones: a row with a sardius, a topaz,
        and an emerald was the first row; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the second row, a turquoise, a sapphire, and a diamond; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They  were enclosed
        in settings of gold in their mountings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There  were  twelve stones according to the names of the sons of
        Israel: according to their names, engraved  like a signet, each one with
        its own name according to the twelve tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they made chains for the breastplate at the ends, like braided
        cords of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They also made two settings of gold and two gold rings, and put the
        two rings on the two ends of the breastplate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they put the two braided chains of gold in the two rings on the
        ends of the breastplate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The two ends of the two braided chains they fastened in the two settings,
        and put them on the shoulder straps of the ephod in the front. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they made two rings of gold and put them on the two ends of the
        breastplate, on the edge of it, which was on the inward side of the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They made two other gold rings and put them on the two shoulder straps,
        underneath the ephod toward its front, right at the seam above the intricately
        woven band of the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Making the Other Priestly Garments'
      title: Making the Other Priestly Garments
      number: 21
      content: And they bound the breastplate by means of its rings to the rings
        of the ephod with a blue cord, so that it would be above the intricately
        woven band of the ephod, and that the breastplate would not come loose from
        the ephod, as the Lord had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He made the robe of the ephod of woven work, all of blue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And there  was an opening in the middle of the robe, like the opening
        in a coat of mail, with a woven binding all around the opening, so that it
        would not tear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They made on the hem of the robe pomegranates of blue, purple, and
        scarlet, and of fine woven linen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And they made bells of pure gold, and put the bells between the pomegranates
        on the hem of the robe all around between the pomegranates: '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: a bell and a pomegranate, a bell and a pomegranate, all around the
        hem of the robe to minister in, as the Lord had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They made tunics, artistically woven of fine linen, for Aaron and
        his sons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'a turban of fine linen, exquisite hats of fine linen, short trousers
        of fine woven linen, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: and a sash of fine woven linen with blue, purple, and scarlet thread,
        made by a weaver, as the Lord had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then they made the plate of the holy crown of pure gold, and wrote
        on it an inscription like the engraving of a signet:HOLINESS TO THE LORD.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The Work Completed'
      title: The Work Completed
      number: 31
      content: And they tied to it a blue cord, to fasten it above on the turban,
        as the Lord had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Thus all the work of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting was finished.
        And the children of Israel did according to all that the Lord had commanded
        Moses; so they did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they brought the tabernacle to Moses, the tent and all its furnishings:
        its clasps, its boards, its bars, its pillars, and its sockets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'the covering of ram skins dyed red, the covering of badger skins,
        and the veil of the covering; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'the ark of the Testimony with its poles, and the mercy seat; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'the table, all its utensils, and the showbread; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'the pure gold lampstand with its lamps (the lamps set in order),
        all its utensils, and the oil for light; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'the gold altar, the anointing oil, and the sweet incense; the screen
        for the tabernacle door; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'the bronze altar, its grate of bronze, its poles, and all its utensils;
        the laver with its base; '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'the hangings of the court, its pillars and its sockets, the screen
        for the court gate, its cords, and its pegs; all the utensils for the service
        of the tabernacle, for the tent of meeting; '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "and the garments of ministry, to minister in the holy place: the
        holy garments for Aaron the priest, and his sons\u2019 garments, to minister
        as priests."
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'According to all that the Lord had commanded Moses, so the children
        of Israel did all the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Then Moses looked over all the work, and indeed they had done it;
        as the Lord had commanded, just so they had done it. And Moses blessed them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tabernacle Erected and Arranged'
      title: The Tabernacle Erected and Arranged
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the Lord  spoke to Moses, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COn the first day of the first month you shall set up the tabernacle
        of the tent of meeting. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall put in it the ark of the Testimony, and partition off the
        ark with the veil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall bring in the table and arrange the things that are to be
        set in order on it; and you shall bring in the lampstand and light its lamps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall also set the altar of gold for the incense before the ark
        of the Testimony, and put up the screen for the door of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then you shall set the altar of the burnt offering before the door
        of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall set the laver between the tabernacle of meeting and
        the altar, and put water in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You shall set up the court all around, and hang up the screen at the
        court gate.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall take the anointing oil, and anoint the tabernacle
        and all that is in it; and you shall hallow it and all its utensils, and
        it shall be holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall anoint the altar of the burnt offering and all its utensils,
        and consecrate the altar. The altar shall be most holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And you shall anoint the laver and its base, and consecrate it.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThen you shall bring Aaron and his sons to the door of the
        tabernacle of meeting and wash them with water. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall put the holy garments on Aaron, and anoint him and consecrate
        him, that he may minister to Me as priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And you shall bring his sons and clothe them with tunics. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "You shall anoint them, as you anointed their father, that they may
        minister to Me as priests; for their anointing shall surely be an everlasting
        priesthood throughout their generations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Thus Moses did; according to all that the Lord had commanded him,
        so he did.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it came to pass in the first month of the second year, on the
        first day of the month, that the tabernacle was raised up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Moses raised up the tabernacle, fastened its sockets, set up its
        boards, put in its bars, and raised up its pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he spread out the tent over the tabernacle and put the covering
        of the tent on top of it, as the Lord had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He took the Testimony and put it into the ark, inserted the poles
        through the rings of the ark, and put the mercy seat on top of the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And he brought the ark into the tabernacle, hung up the veil of the
        covering, and partitioned off the ark of the Testimony, as the Lord had commanded
        Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He put the table in the tabernacle of meeting, on the north side
        of the tabernacle, outside the veil; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and he set the bread in order upon it before the Lord, as the Lord
        had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He put the lampstand in the tabernacle of meeting, across from the
        table, on the south side of the tabernacle; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and he lit the lamps before the Lord, as the Lord had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He put the gold altar in the tabernacle of meeting in front of the
        veil; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and he burned sweet incense on it, as the Lord had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He hung up the screen at the door of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And he put the altar of burnt offering before the door of the tabernacle
        of the tent of meeting, and offered upon it the burnt offering and the grain
        offering, as the Lord had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He set the laver between the tabernacle of meeting and the altar,
        and put water there for washing; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and Moses, Aaron, and his sons would wash their hands and their feet
        with  water from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Whenever they went into the tabernacle of meeting, and when they
        came near the altar, they washed, as the Lord had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: The Cloud and the Glory'
      title: The Cloud and the Glory
      number: 33
      content: And he raised up the court all around the tabernacle and the altar,
        and hung up the screen of the court gate. So Moses finished the work.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then the cloud covered the tabernacle of meeting, and the glory of
        the Lord filled the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And Moses was not able to enter the tabernacle of meeting, because
        the cloud rested above it, and the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Whenever the cloud was taken up from above the tabernacle, the children
        of Israel would go onward in all their journeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But if the cloud was not taken up, then they did not journey till
        the day that it was taken up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: For the cloud of the Lord  was above the tabernacle by day, and fire
        was over it by night, in the sight of all the house of Israel, throughout
        all their journeys.
      comments: []
